column13: Of course, I use it in my hair. I used to spend extra money to buy shampoos with jojoba oil in them.
column14: I love Jojoba Oil! I use it pretty much all over my body at some point during a weeks' time. I use it on my lips to keep them soft and keep that rough line of rough skin off my lips. With Jojoba oil, my lips are still soft & supple....even as a senior citizen. I rub it on my nails & cuticles (both hands and feet) about once a week. It has helped my nails grow stronger and my cuticles look healthy and pretty. I no longer HAVE to wear polish to make them look "half-way" decent. With this oil, my nails look terrific.  Of course, I use it in my hair. I used to spend extra money to buy shampoos with jojoba oil in them. Now, I don't have to do that. About once a week the night before I'm going to wash my hair, I rub jojoba oil on my scalp and in my hair. I then either put on a night cap or I sleep with a towel on my pillow. I think this makes more of it stay on my hair. The next morning, I wash my hair as usual and my hair is just shiny enough...not too slick and definitely not dry.... just healthy looking.  I have used the JOJOBA OIL from TTA Brands for about 10 days now and love it. I love the size because I can put it in my purse... now, that's a statement in itself! I have used other jojoba oils but I would NEVER put them in my purse because most of them leak. THIS one doesn't. It has some kind of special cap (I guess) that makes the jar leak free. I still put it in a plastic bag just to be sure but I take it along with me. If I'm out someplace and my lips start to get chapped, I just put a small dot on my finger and rub it on my lips. Within minutes, my lips are no longer chapped.  Oh! And, I rub it on my skin...especially my arms. You can see by the photo that it only takes a couple of drops (these are really pretty small drops, too.) With those two little drops, I can massage the jojoba oil from the tips of my fingers up and beyond my elbows. Always the elbows... it keeps that rough skin away from my elbows.  I am totally & completely sold on jojoba oil andthe TTA Brands oil hasn't let me down. I don't see how it could because it is 100% pure, organic cold pressed, unrefined - PREMIUM quality Jojoba Oil. And that's what makes jojoba oil good.  I was fortunate to receive this product at a discount in exchange for my HONEST & UNBIASED opinion. I ALWAYS pretest every product prior to writing a review. I am free to write whatever I believe to be true, whether positive or negative. This is my true story and my honest opinion.

column14:
This set includes 5 stainless steel tools (4 loop tools and one lance) in a black polyurethane case. The tools seem to be good quality and sturdy. Being new to this type of kit, I wish there were instructions for use included but unfortunately there is not but after a bit of online research, I found some easy to follow instruction. The tools are fairly easy to use and grip but they do take some practice and a bit of care to do. Just like using your fingers, you can damage your skin and create infections if you are not careful. These should be disinfected prior to using and each time you want to use to minimize infections. If it best I have found to practice on areas that are not as noticeable until you get the hang of it as with too much pressure you can really mark you skin and you don’t want to cause issues with your skin especially on your face. These do work especially for those tough areas to reach but again should be used with care.

column6: Not Your Mothers Kinky Moves Hair Cream 4 Ounce (Curl Define) (118ml)
column13: Amazing. Lost fuzzy frizz gained curls
column14:
I perm my hair to get light spiral curls. My hair is normally straight, fine and thin, and the sides are white-grey while the back is healthy and has a little grey in it. The back keeps its curl definition but the sides tend to frizz up after the perm because of being grey. If I air dry my hair, the sides look good until I either pick it or a little time passes. It won't take long before it gets fuzzy rather than curly.

I've tried everything to keep the fuzzy frizz under control from oils to heavy conditioners. All that did was give me oily frizz! I saw this product the other day so gave it a try. It isn't expensive so was worth a shot. All I can say is "WOW" because the sides now have the same curl definition as the back. Even if I pick it out a bit, it keeps the curl and looks healthy and shiny. I dampened the sides (not much) and rubbed about a nickel size blob on my hands then on the sides (in other words, my hair wasn't wet). I had enough left over that I ran it through the back, too. My hair looks amazing - all curl, no frizz. And the curls are not "crunchy" After my hair dries I lightly run my fingers through my curls go fluff them out and I'm good to go. I love this stuff! So much I came here and ordered 4 more to keep on hand. I never want to run out!

column6: Premium Hair Sponge / Brush For Dreads & Afros, Coils & Magic Twists by Cherir
column14: My son has been growing his hair out for a couple months now and he has been asking for me to do something with it. So when I came across this product I was excited and what made it even better was that I was given the opportunity to receive the Cherir Premium Hair Sponge for free in exchange for my review and honest opinion. So here it goes.....   When I first received it I was excited and opened it up right away and decided to give it a try on my son's (dry) hair just to see what if anything would happen and as I already expected nothing really happened so we waited until after shower time and decided to give it another try. Well... After the shower and the normal routine of washing and applying product we sat down and gave the sponge another try well I tried my hardest to get it to show me some kind of result at the rate I was going something would have been better than nothing! I was starting to get frustrated because I read review after review and watched a few videos so I had to be doing something wrong. So I kept trying and just when I started to see little twists forming and continue ahead with the process I somehow made it worse and undid what I started. At this point I needed a break and yes this might give some of you reading this a laugh I called in my 15 year old daughter and asked her to give it a try because she had watched a few of the videos with me. Well she got right to it and within a few mins we started to see it work. It had made very nice, cute, evenly spaced twists. I would say to anyone ready to give up when they don't see immediate results to take a step back breathe and then try again because as skeptical as I was this product really does work and does exactly when it claims to do. I would definitely recommend this to others.   *I received this product for free in exchange for my review and honest opinion*

column14:
I have never tried Elmers glue or anything like that. I've always been very hesitant when it comes to putting products on my skin, so I've always used nailpolishes remover and washed my hands thoroughly instead.
This product I've come to love in just a matter of minutes. I've had it for weeks now, I bought it from the original website.
If you're looking for something that will blow you away and make nailart 10x faster, this is definitely the product for you. I made a collage and totally overdid my finger, so you can get an idea of how great this product is.
The best part; it came off in one piece.
The only downfall is that yes, the brush might get chunky. If it ever happens to you, you can super easily take a qtip and remove it. It'll look completely new.
Always remember to close it real tight.
Something else I really like about this particular product is that the brush is just like a nailpolish brush. It makes it really easy to get all around.
I know it took the developer multiple months, she tried it on herself and she tested out 6 different liquid latex products and she sent this to 35 nail artists before she started selling it, to make sure they all liked it.
This was not done by someone that just wanted to get a brand out like big companies. There was a lot of thought put into this.
If you're still questioning wether or not to buy this, I suggest checking out her website; nailcarehq.com

[[VIDEOID:96d1f86a40530ecbdadfae3b92ccf4b9]] ★ i received this product at a discount for my honest and unbiased review. I was not influenced by anyone in any way.

🌟 UPDATED: 6/26/2016 - I got this diffuser August 2015. Almost a year ago. I keep it in my front 2nd bathroom and I use it on a daily basis. I fill it with a favorite essential oil and turn it on. Sometime twice a day, but usually just once. But it has been really great so far. Absolutely love it still. Just wanted to update on how it's going.
--------------
I have several diffusers now and they seem to just get better. I think so far this one is my favorite. I like the way it's designed and the way it feels. I know that might sound funny, but it just feels nice. This ZAQ Allay Litemist Aromatherapy Essential Oil Diffuser lets out a lot of nice mist but no condensation, which is really good. I don't like those that by the time you have left it on for an hour, you area of where the diffuser is like a pool of water.
I put this one in my living room and add a few drops o my lavender essential oil and it actually fills the enter room of nice aroma, which I was surprised. In my video I said "small" room but after leaving it on all day today, it was nice to have an aroma throughout the house just from one difusser.

✔️ OVERALL: This diffuser would make a great wedding shower gift. It comes gift ready and I feel that this diffuser is a really good buy.
---------

column13: Marketing proves truth, great shaver with total package
column14:
After using the Braun Series 9 shaver for a week, it has definitely lived up to the claims of not destroying my face or shaving in agony after 3 days of beard growth. It had to live up to a tall standard as I was using the previous top model of Braun. While it has slimmed down in design, it is far more comfortable to hold, and works really well on my face with a full beard. It is gentle to not snag beard hair that I want to retain, but gives a close smooth shave each time.
A couple of design features, one minor, the other more important. The trimmer in the rear of the device is smaller than previous models, so it takes longer to use on a full face. Works well, but more time consuming, minor detail. More importantly the charging and cleaning station is much lower material craftsmanship than previous models. It literally broke when I attempted to connect the charging cord to the station! I had to disassemble the station and reconnect everything. Perhaps just a one off issue, but not fun when you receive a new toy and want to use it. One the plus side, much prettier and MUCH quieter than previous models.
Please note that I received the product as part of a promotion from the brand.

column6: Braun Series 9 9090cc Men's Electric Foil Shaver / Electric Razor with Cleansing Center, Razors, Shavers, & Cordless Shaving System
column14:
This review is based on the Braun Series 9 9090cc Electric Shaver that I was chosen to test, and that I received completely FREE from Braun.
I haven't used an electric shaver in 10 years, so I was a little hesitant to test the Braun Series 9 9090cc at first. My old electric shaver would literally pull longer hairs instead of gently cut.
I had no need to worry, Braun has produced an incredible product in the Series 9.
Out of the Box: The Shaver is beautifully designed, perfectly Slim, Solid Build and Weight but not overly heavy, great to hold, you can feel the quality that's gone into producing the Shaver.
During the first charge The Shaver was at Full Charge within an hour as stated.
After switching on the shaver a gentle Buzzing sound began, with a delicate vibration, unlike the noisy Shavers of times gone by.
I had 4 days worth of growth on my face so this was definitely a Big test for the Series 9, but I had nothing to worry about, the 4 specialized cutters glided through the long hair and stubble like a knife through butter, quiet a lot of my face was clean in one pass.
I probably spent a good 7 minutes or so shaving, which to me is an incredibly fast shave considering the 4 days of hair and stubble I had on my face. The Series 9 glided effortlessly over the contours of my face, the Shaver did all the hard work, all I did was hold and guide it.
I have sideburns, I couldn't get a tight shave right up to the bottom of my side burns but the Long Hair Trimmer made light work of that and a nice tight cut was produced. I did have a couple of ingrowing hairs left over, but I don't know of any Shaver that can deal with those, that's so minor it's hardly worth mentioning really.
In past experience I always found under my nose a tricky place to Shave, but with the locking mechanism on the pivoting head it was very easy to shave in that area, one pass and it was clear of stubble.
Not once during the shave did I feel any discomfort, chafing or irritation from the cutters or foil, it really was a surprising and wonderful shaving experience. After shaving there was no redness or sore areas on my face at all.
I checked to see how closely the Specialized Cutting Elements cut the hair, I was surprised to see that it was just as close a cut as I get when I use my disposable razor, I was very impressed.
Cleaning the Series 9 was a breeze and also very fast, after following the instructions closely I used the small brush to remove stubble, hair and dust from the pivoting head and gently tapped the Foil and Cutter Cassette to remove excess stubble, very simple, very fast.
A small single droplet icon appeared on the shavers display informing me to use the Clean & Charge Station. The Station isn't of the same quality as the Shaver itself, but no need to worry, it does exactly what it says on the box, very well.
It's very simple to install the shaver, it fits like a glove in the station, you press one button and the Station goes into automatic Clean mode.
After 2-3 minutes the Cleaning cycle ends and then the Drying fan starts, the Series 9 was Clean, Dry and fully charged again with in an hour, very impressive.
Over time you do have to replace the cleaning fluid cartridge, Braun recommend every 8 weeks, but if you thoroughly clean the Shaver with the brush and get out as much hair and dust as possible manually, I think you can make the Cleaning Fluid last a little longer, especially if like me you don't shave daily.
On top of everything else provided in the box one extra element that impressed me was the carry case for the Shaver, lightweight but incredibly sturdy and strong.
As far as Pro's go, the whole product impressed me, the Look, Feel, Weight, Quality, Shave and Cleaning process of the Series 9 went beyond my expectations.
If there is one slight Con, it would be the Price, at around $400 it might put a few people off, but that really is minor, you're paying for a very high quality product.
I'm Impressed, and look forward to my next shave.

Now, for the most part I can take a lot of pain but when it comes to piercings and tattoos I'd rather take whatever steps I can to alleviate unnecessary suffering, especially when our vacation is at stake. She followed the directions and washed the aread thoroughly then applied the Lidocaine as instructed. The instructions suggest covering the lidocaine with saran wrap but she was getting her ear pierced in 2 places - the helix and tragus so that was simply not a possibility but didn't seem to make a big difference because the area was completely numb after about 45 minutes so we headed to the boardwalk to do the deed. We arrived at the piercing place about an hour and a half after the application and she said she never felt a thing during either piercing and even ended up repeating the procedure the next day to get her rook and anti-tragus pierced, all pain free. We're planning on getting tattoos in a few weeks and will be using Lidocaine once again, I would definitely recommend this product. On a side note, my future daughter in law gets sun burned very easily and for the most part aloe works but she had gotten really badly burned on her shoulders so I applied the lidocaine and instant relief.

column13: Works nicely on real African American hair
column14:
wow is all I can say. I waited 3 weeks to write a review and after swimming in the ocean and pool to make sure it's the bomb. Bam ! It is. My preteen was tired of the kiddy hairstyles I was doing to her 100% natural hair. I was totally against a relaxer/perm and didn't like the formaldehyde horror stories I'd heard about Keratin treatment.

So I did my research and found Japanese thermal reconditioning treatment and thought it was a happy medium. Not as harsh as a relaxer/perm but not as week and more long lasting than keratin treatment. My daughter does not like to do her hair. Let me rephrase-she hates doing her hair. She will walk out the house looking like buckwheat if I let her (she walked to the park like that)!

Now let me say there must be strong chemicals in it cause it stinks! Definitely have windows n doors open! I took my time followed directions to the "T" and 4 hours later voilà!!! She loves it and now actually does her own hair. I'm happy she's happy and my 3 other daughters are happy! I've heard that some say u should not do this on African American hair but it can definitely be done I bought the normal and left it on for 30 minutes and only left the neutralizer on for 5! So please don't listen to others who say it's not for our hair. This product is for All people regardless of race or hair type. Just choose the right one and you will look as beautiful as my baby!

column6: Makeup Brush Holder by Bella and Bear - Perfect as a Brush Holder for Travel and as a Decorative Addition to your Vanity
column14:
Bella & Bear have certainly done it again. I am slowly but surely building up my Bella & Bear collection. I'm the proud owner of the makeup bag and now I have the makeup brush holder. I love this brand and the collection is very cute and stylish. As always Bella & Bear pay attention to details big and small. This makeup brush holder certainly does not disappoint.

The make up brush holder comes in a very cute box that has the same classic Bella & Bear floral print as the holder itself. This holder can fit quite a few brushes. As a makeup junkie I have lots of brushes but only a few are worthy to sit upon the throne of Bella & Bear. I picked out a cute 10 piece brush set I have and tried it out inside the brush holder. As you can see from the pictures the brushes match the holder perfectly, but that's not what this review is about. Even with 10 brushes in the holder there is still more room for another 10 brushes, maybe more. The holder is tall enough to fit full-size brushes and even has a top so that you can take it with you on-the-go. I love that on the sides of the holder there are snaps to make sure your brushes are safe and secure inside. This brush holder will sit on my vanity in style with the top off for all the world (or whoever comes into my room) to see the awesomeness that is Bella & Bear, and how cute it matches my brushes. When I need to hit the road, whether it be a vacation or a overnight stay with my boyfriend all I need to do is attach the top, secure the snaps and throw in my overnight bag along with matching Bella & Bear makeup bag. This brand makes high quality products that will be adored by me for years to come.

column14:
If you love the smell of basil, just opening the bottle will make you close your eyes in bliss. It did for me! This is very fresh smelling and is genuine/undiluted basil oil. I read that it's good at reducing itching from insect bites, so I rubbed some on a particularly annoying bite on my ankle and it does seem to have helped. People also use it in cooking, for cold symptoms, to help relieve stress and depression, to enhance mental clarity, for motion sickness, and more. While I was reading about this oil I noted that people have used it for pain relief; and the next day I got a toothache. I've long used rosemary oil and clove oil applied to the gums to help toothaches, but they take a while to work. I tried a smidge of basil (straight - you are not supposed to use it undiluted, but I did) and it provided very fast pain relief. I would still use rosemary and clove as they help fight the inflammation and infection causing the pain, but the basil is a great way to knock out the pain.

As a product tester I received this free or virtually so for evaluation and review. This does NOT mean this is a fake review. I was not paid for my review, or given any incentive or reward for a positive review. If you don't believe me, click my profile and scroll down to see the poor reviews I've given bad products. My job is to give an honest opinion, not help the manufacturer. My remarks are sincere and my own.

column6: HealthyWiser - Retinol Serum Clinical Strength 2.5%, Advanced Formula with Hyaluronic Acid, Vitamin E, Green Tea, Correcting Serum for Wrinkles and Fine Lines, Best Therapeutic Skin Care Product
column13: Sounds like a gold mine of a beauty product
column14:
A few years ago I read that using a retinol treatment was essential to maintaining healthy skin. Because it made skin cells turn over it also helped repair and prevent wrinkles, age spots, acne scars, minimized pores, and provided a brighter and more even complexion. Sounds like a gold mine of a beauty product, right? I went for it and added retinol to my daily skin care routine and it was all true. My skin always looks its best when I use retinol at night. However, a good quality retinol treatment is a bit expensive, so I was happy to find HealthyWiser Advanced Retinol Serum, which is an affordable, comprehensive retinol product. I received it complimentary in return for my honest opinion.

Made in the USA with natural and organic ingredients, the unique formula of HealthyWiser Advanced Retinol Serum includes Hyaluronic Acid, Green Tea, and Vitamin E (which is helpful to soothe and protect fragile skin when using a retinol treatment). While I've only ever used a retinol cream, this product is a serum, with a texture almost gel-like, and it smooths on so well. It comes in a dark amber glass bottle which helps protect the integrity and longevity of the product, and it uses a dropper for application. I haven't been able to get the dropper to work very well with the consistency of the serum, so I usually just use it as a dipper.

I've got to say, I've been really happy with this retinol serum. My skin is always brighter and I feel like it does all it promises to do! My tip for using this product is to apply at night and be sure to use a lightweight sunscreen during the day. Like I mentioned above, retinol turns skin cells over and so your skin will be much more prone to sun burns and damage!

The smell is so strong you only need a few drops so a little bit can go a long way. I purchased this pine oil because I love to use it for cleaning. I use the pine to make my own household cleaner, (you know the kind, it has pine in the name), I also use it to make toilet bombs, and wash the walls. After a afternoon of cleaning the whole house smells nice and fresh. Also with the holiday season upon us soon this oil will definitely be very useful.

Pine oil also has health benefits. You can add a few drops to a bath, oil diffuser, face steamer or even a cotton ball and smell periodically throughout the day to help with asthma, coughing, and bronchitis. You can also add the pine oil to a carrier oil for pain relief from arthritis and sore muscles. I love that pine oil scent and it's great because it has a multitude of uses. I think it is a household staple.

column13: Only a very slight resemblance to Creed Silver Mountain Water
column14: I would describe this as having only  a very, very faint resemblance to Creed's Silver Mountain Water.  A previous reviewer said it was about 80% resemblance....I would say it's more like 10%.  I suspect this is made with essential oils as it has a slightly oily feel on the skin. I would describe it as more of a patchouli scent.  It lasts for a very long time so if you like it you can wear it all day, however the scent is very strong and should be used in moderation.  I put a few rolls on and found myself washing it off later as it was pretty overpowering.  I find the bottle and applicator to be really cool.  I wish all colognes came in a bottle like this as it gives you greater control when applying.  However, I ultimately was disappointed in the scent.  If you are looking for Silver Mountain Water you are probably off with the real stuff.  If you are ok with the fact that this really slightly resembles Silver Mountain Water than I think you might be happy with it.  I think you really just need a small dab of the stuff and its somewhat pleasant.  Truth be told my wife likes it so I'll probably keep wearing it.  The fact that you can only put on a little bit means this small vial will likely last a long time.

column14:
I started having a bad breakout this summer when I stopped taking the medication by dermatologist recommended (I was kinda scared of the side effects,that's why). So I did some research online and found something that's missing on my skin care regimen- cleansing oil. I found this cleansing oil from watching YouTube and quickly ordered one from amazon. I could say that it's one of the best skin care products I have tried. My breakouts did not only disappear from one week of using it, but it has pretty much calmed down my sensitive skin. It does an excellent job in removing make up (I also use it for eye make up) and leaves my face feeling clean (but not dry) before I even use my facial cleanser. I have suffered from sunburn in my face from failure to use sunblock in the past, but this cleansing oil has some brightening effects that made my skin tone more even.

The only downside I could think of is that it stings my eyes a little bit. But I have very sensitive eyes to begin with so I'm not sure if this happens to other users. The pros are much more helpful though.

This is the first item from The Face Shop skin care line that I have ever used. But since I'm very impressed with this cleansing oil, I ordered their facial foam wash today at amazon. Hoping to get amazing results from this as well!

column6: Vitamin C Serum by Defy Naturals - 20% Clinical Strength Potency - Organic Vitamin C / Hyaluronic Acid / Amino Complex - ANTI AGING Formula Lets You Defy Your Age Everyday! Eliminate Lines, Wrinkles, Aging Skin and Crows Feet. No Fillers or Additives. 100% Satisfaction Guarantee! (Original Organic, 1 Oz)
column13: I like the packaging of the product
column14:
Today I am reviewing a new Defy Naturals Vitamin C Serum 20% Hyaluronic Acid Amino Complex. This is probably at least the fifth product with hyaluronic acid that I have come across. The products that contain hyaluronic acid are some of the most popular products right now due to the main ingredient – hyaluronic acid – making remarkable effects on the skin. There is a lot of general buzz in the beauty care industry about serums containing hyaluronic acid, and I was so excited to try this one.

In this particular complex there is also Vitamin C serum addition that complements the hyaluronic acid, and assists in slowing the aging process of skin, and repairing skin damage.

I have been using this complex for a few weeks now, and I usually apply it on a cleansed face morning and night, and then apply a moisturizer and sunblock.

I have to say that after a few weeks of use of this serum I do see improvement in my skin tone and overall skin appearance.

I like the packaging of the product, I find it looks more like a pharmaceutical to me, so adds more credibility to the brand in my opinion. The colors of the packaging are all various tones of green. This product is not organic, but it has not been tested on animals, it is made in the USA, and it is vegan. The packaging looks very similar to many other hyaluronic serums I have seen. It is very much in line with other similar products, and so I wish it looked a little more sleek maybe. I would buy this for myself, but I am not sure if I were to use it as a gift, as it does not look fancy enough for a gift in my opinion.

The container with the serum has a convenient pipette for easier application. The serum does not have any scent. The serum is very mild on my skin, and I haven’t noticed any irritations. The serum has very liquidy texture, it seems that I am applying oil or water on my face, but it does not leave any shine, or residue, and is absorbed in the skin very well.

I would give this product 4 out of 5 stars! This is a nice product with hyaluronic acid, and it is very affordable!

I have received this product for free in order to review it.

column6: Generic Oral-B Deep Sweep Replacement Electric Toothbrush Head - For an Innovative Cleaning- 4 Pack- By PAZ Generix®
column13: Not all generics are the same
column14:
I'm all about buying generic because I strongly think that generics are usually the same (sometimes better) than the real thing. I'm never deterred by generics so I wasn't deterred by these when I needed more brush heads. Unfortunately these are NOT like the "real thing", the bristles feel very weird and that's understandable for the price, but even with the price point, if I were to keep buying these, I would spend more money than buying the original brush heads.

I had to replace the first head after about 4 days because it stopped moving from side to side, it was stuck in one position which did nothing for cleaning my teeth, the second head lasted 2 days, same problem. Everyone knows that you need to take off the brush head and rinse it off after a brush because toothpaste does get inside it, it's even in the instructions of the tooth brush itself that you should take off the brush head and rinse it off. These are not built to be taken off and on the brush, like the originals are, because by the time I got to the third brush head I decided I'd stop rinsing the brush head by taking it off the toothbrush, this has worked and the third brush head has been going for around a week. Nevertheless, this seems kind of gross because I don't want there to be stale, dried up toothpaste inside the brush head.

I've ordered the brand name brush heads and should be getting them soon, I think I will have the remaining brush head from this pack as an emergency replacement. I'm glad I bought the 4-pack first rather than the bigger pack because I'm sad to say that these were kind of a waste of money. Good thing they're not expensive.

column13: If that's not great customer service I don't know what is
column14:
When the first shipment arrived, the whole box smelt strong and the content of the spray was totally empty. I think the content leaked out during shipment. I was frustrated because I was going to take it on my trip and the shipment itself took a few days to arrive in the first place. However after I contacted the seller, the seller sent the replacement overnight immediately and gave me a refund. If that's not great customer service I don't know what is! As for the product I am very happy with also. The spray is like a light mist, and does a great job holding the style but without making it look unnatural or stiff. I also like the fact that you can restyle your hair during the day by combing or using your fingertips. Yes, it's more pricey than your regular hairspray, but this isn't your regular hairspray and well worth it! The sprayhead is pretty nice too as you can lock it so it doesn't spray out if you were to stick it in your bag:)

***UPDATE 9/18/2015 : I initially gave it 5 stars but I had to change it to 3 stars for two reasons...
1) Soon after, the spay started clogging up. It instructs to run under warm water when it did, and it worked a couple of times. But at this point, the only way I could get it to spray is to poke a hole each time with a pin.
2) Although the spray handle is unique and sleek looking, it feels awkward and hard to aim right. The work around for this is just like someone else posted, to press on the top part of the handle instead of squeezing the actual handle.

That being said, I still do like what this does and how the scent isn't overwhelming at all.

column6: Remington PF7500 F5 Comfort Series Foil Shaver, Men's Electric Razor, Electric Shaver
column14:
Having recently tried out another Remington shaver by comparison this shaver offers more.
It provides a closer shave with minimal passes. It also has a nice pivot which makes it easier to hold as well as making it more comfortable at shaving time.
Its Lithium battery holds a charge for 60 minutes and it also has a 5 minute quick charge that is supposed to work in a pinch which I didn't test.
Aside from giving a nice close shave with no detectable stubble, it trims nicely around the neck and sideburns. The battery charge remained consistent but you can also use this corded if necessary.
Clean-up is easy as this can be cleaned under water but swishing the shaving head under water.
While this isn't a high end shaver, it is a good entry level one. It is light yet substantial enough to offer a reasonable life span and it lives up to the manufacturer's promises.

column13: Must have for Cosmetologists and for every day hair styling!
column14:
I received the HSI Professional heat resistant glove just in time to fix my hair for a date night with my husband. I took the glove out of the package and slipped it onto my hand easily. I warmed my flat iron up and proceeded to straighten my hair with ease. I felt warmth thru the glove, but it protected my hand from being burned. I have burned my forehead and fingers before from fumbling around with my hot flat iron. The glove gives you more control and makes it so much easier to hold the fat iron in place. The material is flexible enough to move easily and use your hand normally. I have since tried it with my curling iron and it worked like a charm. I wish I had found this genius item sooner. It took 2 weeks for the burn on my head to heal and it made washing and fixing my hair almost unbearable. Now I just reach for the glove. I really love this glove!
I am a cosmetologist by trade and I think this would be a must have for cosmetologists everywhere who style customers hair daily. I received this product at a discounted price in exchange for your honest and unbiased review.

column13: This is so much more than coconut...
column14:
MaggardRazors sells a sampler pack of ToOBS scents which I'm quite happy I purchased. I NEVER would have tried the coconut if I hadn't. As someone who only somewhat enjoys coconut (coconut everything - milk, flavor, flakes, scent), I will say that this is one of the greatest scents I've ever smelled in my life. It's not pure coconut. There's more to it. I don't have a nose for separating scents like others do, but I'd love to hear what else is actually in this.

As far as the shave itself, ToOBS is popular for a reason. I've used everything from hard soaps to soft creams and this is one of my favorites yet. Something worth noting - this is a thirsty cream. If you feel like you need more, try adding a little more water first. You'll be pleased with how much longer the tub will last.

column6: OZNaturals Tinted Moisturizer, SPF 30 Sunscreen. Broad Spectrum Protection. Zinc Oxide + Minerals In This Tinted Sunscreen Protects, Moisturizes And Blends Well To Provide A Rich, Youthful Glow!
column13: A sunscreen and a make up in one that I now use daily
column14:
Until this product, I have hated all types of sunscreen. They smell terrible. The white color takes awhile to work into your skin. Even then, you still have a hint of the white sunscreen left. The consistency is that of a gunky goop. As a redhead, I have become a sunscreen expert over the years. So many products don't provide enough coverage and still leave me burnt. This sunscreen has solved all of those problems and added extra benefits that make this an necessary item to have.

After purchasing, this sunscreen arrived very quickly. When you squeeze the sunscreen out of the bottle, you notice the light brown tint to it. The consistency is a very smooth even cream that spreads with ease over your skin. The tint to it enables me to easily see where I have applied it. What I didn't realize until I first used it was the makeup application of this product. I can actually use it as a foundation as well as a sunscreen. When you apply the cream to your face, it provides an even tone throughout it. It doesn't leave that heaviness that most foundations leave either. You honestly don't realize that you have anything on in the first place. As a woman who likes it to appear that she has no makeup on, I really enjoyed the double use of this sunscreen. The smell is like a very light lotion smell. Not even close to the strong smelling sunscreen that other products have.

Overall, I am highly please with this. It has become an item that's daily used. I did receive this product at a discounted rate for my honest and unbiased opinion, but that does not discount the amazing benefits to this outstanding product.

column6: Gillette Endurance Antiperspirant and Deodorant
column13: Too many holes, but good at what it does
column14:
I switched to this after Mitchum changed their formula and their tubes. They added a ton more holes to the top and made the gel thinner, which resulted in a huge mess every time I used it.

I swapped to this in hopes of finding something a bit less messy, and it's on the mark for the most part. My only complaint is the number of holes again. It's so easy to turn the dial a fraction of a degree too far and end up with may more product than needed. It seems to especially be an issue with a brand new tube since there's usually a lot of airspace at the top, and transport can cause the gel to be uneven and want to gush out of one side or the other.

Aside from the minor complaint, I'm happy with the product.

My scalp has always been a mess - oily, flaky, and intensely itchy.

After detoxing my hair from all products for six months, I'm now using minimal amounts of all-natural shampoo and conditioner in addition to this product. My scalp has become healthy and manageable for the first time in years. I don't get oily any more AT ALL (I hardly even need to wash it these days, it stays soft and in great condition for a week and a half or longer without any upkeep)

I recommend this product to anyone with scalp issues!

The lovely gel consistency of Alice Nouveau Hydrating Anti-Wrinkle Serum helps not only to moisturize your face and neck, but to help minimize the signs of aging. Wrinkles, fine lines, and skin tone will improve with twice-daily use of this Alice Nouveau serum. Not only that, it reduces the appearance of dark spots and helps prevent clogged pores.

This Alice Nouveau anti-aging serum is a blend of organic and natural ingredients and is free from alcohols, parabens, and sulphates, which may irritate your skin. It contains retinol, hyaluronic acid, green tea, Vitamin E, and jojoba oil. Your serum is manufactured in the USA under strict controls in an FDA approved facility.

Facial serums can give you added moisture and you'll want to use a serum to get added nutrients deeper into the layers of your skin where a regular moisturizer is not able to reach. The antioxidants in your facial serum can take up to 4 weeks to completely soak into the skin and remove toxins that cause dullness, dryness, and discoloration.

The serum comes in a sturdy bottle with a pump that won't clog or break. The lid is tight so not even a drop of serum will be wasted on a spill. Just one pump of the anti-wrinkle serum covers a large area and about two pumps covers your whole face and neck. The 1 fluid ounce bottle should last you for quite some time.

If you're looking for a good quality anti-aging facial serum, then you should get yourself some Alice Nouveau Hydrating Anti-Wrinkle Serum today.

column6: 180 Cosmetics Cellulite Reducing Solution, Orange Peel, 5.1 Oz
column14:
Similar in texture and in effectiveness to the Cellulite Reducing Solution by the same brand, this cream is designed to target any body area that could be firmer, smoother, less wrinkly (if your problem area is the chest, there is a more specific product called Breast Firming Solution). I accepted to test this cream for review purposes with more curiosity than high expectations because my target area is notoriously tough to improve. I had gained weight and then finally lost some, and was doing my best with exercise and my Slendertone belt, but as long as that little cushion of fat remained over my stomach, I could never see the full impact of my efforts.

That's where this cream comes in. My stomach problem was not really cellulite but a different type of subcutaneous fat and very difficult to shift. I must stress that, good as the cream is, it takes time to see results. It will not magically melt away fatty bulges, it will not reduce your waistline measurement all by itself, and it does not claim to remove stretch marks, but it will improve the elasticity and tone of your skin. It can make all the difference when your shape is improving, but the skin texture lets you down. Loose, wrinkly skin is so ageing, as much on the body as it is on the face, but specialist creams like this one are difficult to find. I'm very glad I gave this a try because the improvement, once it starts to show, is very pleasing.

The cream comes in a medium-sized soft tube (150 ml) and has a fairly thick consistency. It becomes very white as you spread it, and stays creamy for a while, allowing a good, long massage, which also helps. Once absorbed, there is no residue. Among the main active ingredients are caffeine, Vitamin C, carnitine, and algae extracts. It smells deliciously of essential oils and, like the rest of the 180 Cosmetics range, it is a natural product without any toxic chemical additives. All their products are also cruelty-free, and not tested on animals.

So, if you have the patience and determination to address your imperfect skin, this product will be a great help, but it will be a very gradual process. Some improvement, however, is easy to see quite quickly. If your skin is at all lined, with surface creases and a general dry look, this cream will make an immediate impact that goes beyond just moisturizing. You will also get the uplifting, mood-improving benefits of massage, even though you are doing it yourself. The only negative I found is that the cap stopped closing after a couple of uses, so I decanted the tube contents into a jar. It seems to me that this cream would be very helpful during weight loss, even more than afterwards, as the skin would not a have a chance to become loose in the first place.you have the patience and determination to address your imperfect skin, this product will be a great help, but it will be a very gradual process. column6: Braun Series 9 9090cc Men's Electric Foil Shaver / Electric Razor with Cleansing Center, Razors, Shavers, & Cordless Shaving System
column14:
I am reviewing the Braun Series 9 9090cc Electric Shaver that I received as part of a product promotion from the brand. Let me start by saying this is a great product. I had my concerns at first, but after a week of using the Braun Series 9 shaver, I'm sold. A little about me: I am dark complected with very thick, course, facial hair. I also shave my head daily. For the past few years, I have been using a double edge safety razor, with a traditional shave cream and brush on my face. On my head I have been using disposable cartridge razors (after trying various razors designed specifically for shaving heads with disastrous results).
When picking up the Braun Series 9 my initial concerns were:
1. Would it give me a close enough shave to compare with the safety razor?
2. Would it irritate my neck and produce razor bumps like other electric razors I have tried in the past did?
3. Would it be quick and versatile enough to shave my head daily?
4. Would it be easy to travel with?
5. Would it be easy to clean and maintain?
After a week of using the Braun Series 9 I can answer yes to each of these questions. The shaver is quick and gentle, providing a close comfortable shave on both my face and head. It quickly attacks the hard to reach stubble on my neck and behind my ears without irritating my skin or leaving shave bumps. It eliminates the mess of shave cream and the time it takes to whip up a good lather. It navigates around my mustache and goatee without snagging and pulling on the hair that I want to keep.
Cleanup is quick and simple. I just drop the shaver into the charging/cleaning station and it does all the work for me.
On the second day that I had the shaver, I had to leave town for a quick, two day, business trip. I put the shaver in the included travel case and tossed it into my overnight bag. Traveling with the Braun Series 9 was significantly easier, cleaner and more compact than with my previous shaving kit and the charge was more than enough to last a couple of days without recharging.
In short, I would definitely recommend the Braun Series 9 shaver without hesitation.t a couple of days without recharging. In short, I would definitely recommend the Braun Series 9 shaver without hesitation.

For all I know, this product may work great in addition to their shampoo or whatever. Frankly, it seems more like a scam to be. Buyers beware, steer away.

Edit: In case anyone is wondering how I know the reviews are fake. Another reviewer made it pretty clear - all the other reviewers have given similar 5 star reviews on all the same type of products (programming, pet related things, all the same...often times even the same books).

column14:
After having kids, my belly isn't what it used to be. I decided to give the anti cellulite cream (more of a cross between a cream and a gel) a shot and see if I could help the issue. The cream is orange and tingles. When you wipe it on the skin, it feels warm at first, then minty and cool. It feels like ice almost. The ingredients are mostly organic (87%) and they work very quickly. I noticed within a day or two, having used a small amount a few times a day, my skin already looks tighter and healthier. I wouldn't use this at night as it makes it hard to sleep when your skin feels like ice. It reminds me of the feeling when you have a mint and then drink cold water. The jar is a good enough size that it should last about a month since you don't need a ton of it.

column6: Davines Alchemic Golden Shampoo 8.45oz
column13: Tressa and Blond Brilliance are better.
column14: This didn't do much for my golden blond color treated hair.  It didn't add a lot of golden color but it's a decent cleansing shampoo nonetheless and I used the entire bottle, although I won't repurchase it.  I have a big problem with the glass bottle, which gets slippery in the shower and it's rather dangerous.  I don't know why any company would package a shampoo in a glass bottle.  I also used the golden conditioner and even together, they didn't make much of an impact.  Again, the conditioner is in a jar, which is awkward to unscrew with wet hands and again, it's glass.  This is a problem for me and regardless of the fact that the shampoo and conditioner didn't work very well, I would never again have glass containers in the shower.  I've found a much better product in Tressa Watercolors shampoo in the golden tone.  It lathers like crazy, is sulfate free and definitely adds nice golden color when left on for 5-10 minutes.  Also good is Blond Brilliance lathering toner in the warm tone. Also sulfate free, it leaves my hair soft and shiny and it lathers really well and smells divine.  These two brands work much better than Davines and both are less expensive.  I purchased the Tressa shampoo on Amazon and Blond Brilliance is at Sally Beauty Supply.  I found that both of these products are superior to Davines and neither comes in a glass container, lol!  I recommend Davines only for cleansing and not for adding color.  Tressa and Blond Brilliance both add a lot of color and both keep my hair in really good condition and full of shine.

Not sure of the quality difference, but I have to come to the conclusion that new and improved does not always mean better (Think old Coke and New Coke, as well as Ragu sauce, that I loved until they changed it to a "new and improved" taste.)

Anyway, the price is great. Three jars for $30 as opposed to one jar for $17 at the store. Also, my wife preferred the older purple cream that these are and was upset over the change and she is now glad she got the purple cream.

I guess we men just get distinguished looking, whereas women simply degrade and fall apart. (I supposed I should order a Snuggie now just in case she reads that last comment.) Someone stated that this stuff was meant for the asian market, whereas the white stuff is for us Americans. Well hell, if this will make my wife look more like one of them hot asian women, well, tell me where I can buy a five gallon bucket and dunk my wife's big fat.....errr I mean have enough on hand for my beautiful bride of over 30 years so she will never run out...OMG...thirty...really?

So yes, older formula, but unless someone can tell me the difference in performance from this and the newer and improved stuff, I'll take that savings and use it to make my couch more comfortable, or maybe some anti-snoring products or diet pills or exerciser things (does Suzanne Somers still sell them butter-master thing-a-ma-jigs) for the wifewhen (if) she lets me back in bed.

column6: Majestic Pure Grade A Unrefined Organic Shea Butter, 12 oz
column14:
I purchased the Majestic Pure Grade A Unrefined Organic Shea Butter because I have seen a few things on Pinterest that we have wanted to make with it. We ended up making Shea Lotion Bars, which were very simple.
The block I received did have a slight odor that I didn't really care for. It was very subtle and when we mixed the Butter with other oils and scents you could no longer smell the original scent. Ingredients
2 ounces (1/4 cup) shea butter
2 ounces (1/4 cup) beeswax pastilles
3 tablespoons coconut oil
10 drops of essential oils of your choice (optional)

Instructions
In a double boiler, melt shea butter and beeswax over medium low heat. (I just used a large glass bowl sitting on top of a small pot of water. I’ve also used a Pyrex measuring cup sitting inside a pot of water – this method makes it easy to pour melted lotion base into mold)
When shea butter and beeswax are nearly melted, add coconut oil (which will melt very quickly). Stir. Add essential oils, if desired.
Pour melted lotion base into mold (I used 1.5 inch square brownie molds, but any molds will do) and let cool until completely solid (this will take several hours).
Remove lotion bars from molds and store in a cool, dry place. Note: heat will re-melt the lotion bars, so if for some reason you need to re-mold, just heat and start over.
To use: simply rub lotion bars in between your hands to activate. Your body heat will melt/soften the bars just enough to give you some good lotion to apply anywhere, even your lips! I rub the bars straight onto my lips, just like lip balm.

We also mixed up a quick batch of Eczema Cream to give to a family friend of ours for her son. She said it smelled really good and it actually worked really well. No oily leftovers and easy to wash off in the shower/bath.
Ingredients:
1/4 cup shea butter
1/4 cup coconut oil
15 drops lavender essential oil, therapeutic grade only. (where to buy essential oils)
5 drops tea tree essential oil, therapeutic grade only. (where to buy essential oils)

Directions:
Fill a saucepan halfway full with water. Heat the water over medium high heat ( not boil).
In a small jar add the shea butter and the coconut oil.
Place jar in the saucepan (like a makeshift double boiler) until the oils melt.
Remove the jar and cool for a few minutes to about room temp before adding in the oils.
Mix the essential oil into coconut/shea mixture and put the jar in the fridge until done, should be firm to touch.
You can use the eczema cream at this point, but if you’d like more of a “whipped” body butter lotion then put the oil in a kitchen aid stand mixer and mix on high for several minutes until the eczema cream looks like whipped butter. You may have to scrape the sides of the mixer down a few times. Apply liberally to any affected area of the skin.

I did receive this product for review purposes. All opinions and thoughts are my own and honest.buy essential oils) Directions: Fill a saucepan halfway full with water. column14: I have a 19-month-old blue-eyed, blond-haired, extremely fair-skinned little girl. I have also used it on myself without any problems, and like my daughter, I have very, very pale skin (sometimes even the lightest shade of makeup is too dark for me). I've used tubes that I ordered directly from Honest.com, and I have never purchased it from a retail store or Costco.

column6: serumtologie PURE Whipped Chiffon Anti Aging Moisturizer for Men & Women | Hypoallergenic | Non Greasy & Fragrance Free | Best for Normal, Oily, Combination & Sensitive Skin | 4.5oz
column13: Works better as a body butter. All natural and fluffy!
column14:
This cream is all natural and has a nice whipped consistency. It is light and airy and smells nice. It comes in a huge 4 ounce jar which I have never seen facial products come in. They are usually under 2 ounces. I love the consistency of this cream and I like that there is nothing artificial in it. However, the ingredients, while nourishing, really don't target fine lines and other aging signs. They hydrate, which is a big part of looking youthful, but there aren't antioxidants to ward off free radicals nor are there acids and vitamins that are proven to help with the appearance of fine lines, wrinkles and sagging.

As a moisturizer, this one is good. It isn't greasy and it doesn't cause my skin any irritation. I have been using it more as a body butter than a face cream because I need certain ingredients in my creams. It works beautifully as a body butter. It softens my skin and leaves no residue behind. It's light yet hydrating. For younger skin, this is great on the face. I am 50 and I look for certain ingredients that have been proven to work. I do use serums containing Vitamin C and hyraluranic acid among other things but I still need a heavier and more potent face cream. I will continue to use this beautifully whopped cream on my body and may buy more. It is definitely better than the chemical laden body butters I own now. I will also use it on my face from time to time as it does a nice job of hydrating without being greasy and and it is gentle.

I have to go with my gut though and rate this 3 stars only because it doesn't have what my aging skin needs to help hold back the ends of time. The ingredients are good, don't get me wrong, just not what I personally look for in an anti aging facial cream. But for the body? It's like buttah!

I received this product at a reduced rate in exchange for my evaluation and honest review. Obviously I was not obligated to rate in any certain way and I rated as I felt I should. However, I do recommend this cream to younger people who don't need as many anti aging ingredients and to anyone who wants a great, natural body butter. It may also work for aging facial skin. I just like my creams to have a more proven ingredients in them. All natural though is very desirable and healthy.eople who don't need as many anti aging ingredients and to anyone who wants a great, natural body butter. It may also work for aging facial skin. I just like my creams to have a more proven ingredients in them. All natural though is very desirable and healthy.

column6: Permanent Hair Color Corrector
column13: Best Cure for Unintentional Goth I have found!
column14: And I've needed a cure a few times. I had my hair highlighted sometime back. I have light brown hair as my natural color. Highlighting was offered to me as just a shade lighter than my natural color. And I agreed. Well, despite using color care shampoo, it became bright and brassy pretty quickly. Two attempts in that salon and another one only gave me another weird shade that quickly washed out to brassy again. So after months of just living with it since the last time, I decided enough was enough. I would color it myself. I had someone with me when I bought the permanent hair dye from a store to help me get a good match for my coloring. The test strand looked great, a light warm shade of brown. So, I did it...and my entire head of hair was BLACK - unnatural, looked like I went Goth black. I wore a baseball cap, took a deep breath, and decided to try this product. And yes, it worked! I did a test strand first at 10 minutes. That worked well, pulling out the black to brown., Then I covered my whole hair - minus the test strand - for ten minutes. It turned out great - ALL the black gone, down to a natural looking shade of light brown. Not perfect, but definitely I could live with it now and go out in public without shame and a baseball cap. To me, it does smell AWFUL, just like rotten eggs like someone said. BUT I can bear a bad smell to get my hair looking human on me again.

column6: Wahl Professional Peanut Clipper/Trimmer - Great On-the-Go Trimmer for Barbers and Stylists - Powerful Rotary Motor
column13: I cut my own hair with it. A quality tool for mustaches and beards.
column14:
If I have a few days (or more) of beard stubble, I use this before the razor. This is mainly what I bought it for and it works great, leaves the equivalent of about one day's growth (my growth is about medium, not heavy, not light). I wish I'd had this when I had my beard, it would be an excellent tool for beards. Before I shaved off my mustache, I used the Peanut for trimming and it really worked great! It worked great to shave off the mustache, too. I've removed my mustaches with various tools, and the Peanut is the best yet. I'm a craftsman who enjoys using good quality tools, and this is one of them.

I've had the Peanut for a few months now and have used it to cut my own hair, with great results. One day my hair was way too long and it was time to go to the barber. I figured the barber could fix anything I did with the Wahl if I didn't cut it too short, so I decided to give it a try, and I haven't been to the barber since. I cut it when I haven't washed my hair for a few days. I put on the #4 stand-off and buzz it all over the sides and back (I go over it a few times, pausing to use a comb, until I get it to where it looks okay). I don't go too high up on the sides, just a trimmer-width or less over the ears, and somehow the top always seems to come out fine (staying long enough to part and comb nicely). Without any stand-off, I trim around the ears and trim-up the sideburns. With the #2 stand-off, I do my eyebrows. Using a hand mirror, I scissor off the the hair at the back of my neck if it's too long. Then I give it a good shampoo, and the next day if anything needs a little more trim (which about half the time it does) I give it a quick tune-up with the Wahl, and I'm good for about three weeks. This little baby is going to pay for itself pretty quickly, if it hasn't already.

The Peanut is fairly quiet, too, doesn't hurt my ears at all. I've had three other electric hair clippers (full size) and the Peanut whips them all for sound and clean-cutting. About those other three: one died, one actually broke and fell apart while I was using it, and one is very dull and does not have replaceable blades like the Peanut.

My only CON: I like very pliable cords that tend to hang straight, and this one is a little too stiff and plasticky, but I've seen worse.an-cutting. About those other three: one died, one actually broke and fell apart while I was using it, and one is very dull and does not have replaceable blades like the Peanut.

My only CON: I like very pliable cords that tend to hang straight, and this one is a little too stiff and plasticky, but I've seen worse.

The reason I got the black one is that YouTube gurus recommend it for use with pressed powder foundation, i.e. MAC Studio Fix. column14:
LuxeOrganix Shampoo + Conditioner helps to moisturize your hair whether you’re spending your days in the chlorine of the pool, the salt of the ocean, or under a wool cap when it’s cold with its UV and thermal protectant as well as vitamins and antioxidants. It’s perfect for natural, dry, coarse, fine, curly, or straight hair.

LuxOrganix helps to nourish and repair your hair from the damage of blow dryers, curling irons, straighteners, coloring, and all sorts of products. Your hair will be healthier, shinier, and have a more youthful appearance. And, your hair color will remain more vibrant for a longer period of time.

One of the issues I have with conditioners is that it makes my hair too soft. With LuxeOrganix condition, it doesn’t leave my baby fine hair overly conditioned and soft. I’m still able to use it and then style my hair. The style holds for the whole day with my regular hair care routine.

My favorite thing about this shampoo and conditioner combo is that they smell so good! The scent reminds me of the bubble gum toothpaste that the dentist uses to clean your teeth. Thankfully, I don’t smell like bubble gum all day, though.

LuxeOrganix contains no sulfates, parabens, or sodium chloride; ingredients that are thought to possibly cause itchy scalp and serious skin irritation as well as disease, hair loss, and damage.

A bonus of using LuxeOrganix is that they are a very proactive and communicative company and were great to work with. Not only do I recommend LuxeOrganix Shampoo and Conditioner, I recommend the company, too.

This product was great! I love how it made my legs so smooth. Along with the epilator comes a spray to reduce the painful sensation of removing your hair from the fiolicle, a cord, a size reducer cover for smaller areas, and a cover. After reading the manual they suggest that the best time to use the epilator is after a warm shower to open the pores. I did one leg before the shower and one after to see if there really was a difference between the two and there is alot! The leg that was before the shower was more painful and less short hair was removed (longer hairs had the same result with both of coming out painfully) and the one after the shower was easier and faster to remove. The only down side was the cord was a little to short. I had to keep turning to reach all the parts of my leg. Overall this product did as described.

column6: Facial Cleanser & Anti Wrinkle AHA Cream Cleanser 5% From Uptown Cosmeceuticals, Highly Moisturizing, Effective Skin Care,  Exfoliator, Fights Signs of Aging & Breakouts Revealing Radiant Skin, 4 Oz
column14:
I used this product as a cleanser as that is what is indicated it's use is. However, after reading the Q&A I see that Uptown states to leave it on 5-15 minutes and then wash off. This is not listed anywhere on the box or the jar its self. If this is how it should be used, as a treatment, then that is how it should be marketed, not as a cleanser. I also would prefer to see this in a pump (if a cleanser) or a stand up tube (if a treatment). I don't really care for dipping into jars but I wanted to try this product. Also the directions do need to be larger on the jar as they are tiny and there is plenty of room to make them larger on the label and more obvious.

As a cleanser my face nice after using it to wash; however, when I used toner afterwards, there was still make up on my face and I had to rewash my face with a regular cleanser. While there are no exfoliating 'beads' in this, the AHA is the exfoliater but again, using it as a cleanser I don't think you really get the full benefit of that unless you use something like a Konjac sponge with it. When I used this as a treatment on my already cleansed face, left this on for 5 minutes and then washed it off, I felt it did a much better job and it allowed the cream to do what it is designed to do with regard to cell renewal. Therefore, I believe I will reserve the rest to use as a treatment. Do not use this on or near your eyes to remove eye make up or as part of the treatment.

This product is 80% organic and not tested on animals. This has some really great ingredients such as aloe, Apricot Kernel Oil, Vitamin E, Green Tea, Bilberry, Sugar Cane, Orange, Lemon and Cranberry Extract, Mango Butter, Willow Bark, Neem Oil, and Rosemary Extract. I know that Neem is great as a treatment on the face.

I'm still giving this product 4 stars instead of 3 because it does make a great treatment. However, I didn't give it 5 because I feel the packing of the product and labeling/marketing of it as a correct product (cleanser or treatment) needs some work.

column6: OZNaturals Facial Sunscreen  This Anti Aging SPF 30, Broad Spectrum, Mineral Sunscreen with Zinc Oxide Will Help You Keep That Healthy Youthful Glow!
column14:
The OZ NATURALS SPF 30 AGE BROAD SPECTRUM SUNSCREEN arrived safely and as scheduled.

This SPF30 sunscreen contains 7.5% Octyl Methoxycinnamate and 7% Zinc Oxide as its active ingredients. It is about 6.25 inches tall and lightly scented like most sunscreen does.

When looking for cosmetic products, I always tries to avoid products that contains chemicals. Many sunscreens out in the markets contains 2 to 3 different potentially toxic active ingredients. Octyl Methoxycinnamate is one that can potentially be harmful to your body when exposed to UV rays; it can generates free radicals in skin cells. You can find this ingredients in sunscreens and lip balms. 7.5% is the max. FDA approved amount according to my quick internet search ( Please note I am not an expert or medical professional, please do not rely on this information and always do your own research).

The direction is easy to follow, you simply apply it 15 minutes before sun exposure and reapply it every 2 hours/ 40 minutes after swimming.

Overall, this product contained 1 chemical active ingredient instead of 2 or 3. I appreciate that this product is MADE in the USA and is making steps into making less toxic sunscreen in the market. I also uses a safer alternative active ingredient zinc oxide. I rate this product 4 out of 5 Stars.

*** I received this complimentary product in exchange for my honest and unbiased review. I am not affiliated with the company and did not receive any compensation from them. ***

column6: Veet Warm Sugar Wax Botanic Inspirations, 8.45 Ounce
column13: This is all I use now
column14:
Over the years, I tried a handful of heat and no-heat waxes before settling on the Nair Peach Melon hot wax. I liked it because it was effective and washed off easily with warm (soapy) water. Unfortunately, it was discontinued so I had to renew my search. I tried a few more before discovering this Veet Warm Sugar Wax Botanic Inspirations magic!

This s#%t is rad!!! First, and most Important, if you follow the instructions, it does a great job of removing hair. Second, clean-up is a breeze. Warm water is enough to wash it off your skin as well as the cloth strips. Oh...and did I mention the cloth strips are WASHABLE and REUSABLE! The other day, I waxed my chest and legs (I am a male) and though I needed almost 3 packages worth of the strips to get the job done, at the end, I threw them in the sink and soaked them in warm water and all the wax/hair rinsed out so I can use them all again (Let them dry before putting them away). For that same chest/legs wax job, I only used one tub of wax.

The temperature indicator, I feel, skews a bit to the safe side to keep people from burning themselves. But personally, the "No" indicator was visible the entire time I was using it and I never got burned. Going exactly by the instructions seemed to yield a thicker wax that was more difficult to spread so as the other reviewer indicated, go as warm as you can stand :)

In summation, this is now my go-to product for waxing.

column14:
With a couple of curly-girls in the house, I'm always on the lookout for products to help tame their wild manes. I definitely prefer encouraging the spirals instead of the current trend of straightening it to within an inch of its life. This curl energizing therapy shampoo is one of several Tosca products we're trying together. All of them have a really nice scent. The shampoo lathers up nicely without being too harsh. I found that it truly does boost the curliness factor of your hair BUT I would highly recommend using the detangling and shine leave-in formula right after using this. (Or use another brand, my point is your curls are going to need plenty of moisture and shine after shampooing.)

We love that it isn't tested on animals. It's a little expensive for the small size, but a little does go a long way. We will be keeping this on hand for curl rescue as the new school year begins!

I have received free products to help facilitate my review but all opinions are my own.

column6: Yin-Care Supreme Oral Care 5.1 fl oz (150ml)
column14:
My acupuncturist got this for me because I've been dealing with tons of thrush problems (yeast infection in the mouth, often caused by inhaled Corticosteroids aka inhalers). I brush every time I use my inhaler and use regular mouthwash, but it wasn't stopping the thrush invasion. I didn't have insurance at the time, so going to the regular doctor to get Diflucan or Nystatin or something was out of the question. It has worked for me twice now. The first time took a long while (it was pretty far along before we got this to work on it). This last time, I saw the little spots and tasted that strange taste in my mouth you get with thrush and started this immediately. Twice a day. - I can't stand washing with it for 2 minutes as it tells you to as the taste gets overwhelming. But I take my inhaler, brush my teeth and gently the roof of my mouth. Then rinse with water, rinse with this for about 15-20 seconds, and then rinse with Scope to kill this taste. Tiny bit of water in the front of mouth, avoiding the spots with thrush with the water, and then go about my day or night. - It's killed off the thrush in one week of use this time. All better!

Should note, I also was told to use probiotic pills at the same time. As I take them on and off constantly, I can't testify to if this is due to a combo of this mouthwash and the probiotic pills or just the mouthwash. Either way, I'll take the win!

It's a natural alternative to antibiotics and I'm thrilled to have something OTC I can use.

column6: Bath & Body Works Japanese Cherry Blossom Couture Limited Edition Eau de Parfum 3.4 fl oz
column13: Couture Limited Edition No. 3 - the best version of Japanese Cherry Blossom
column14:
Japanese cherry blossom is my favorite fragrance from Bath and Body Works, and this interpretation of it is, without a doubt, the best one. Every so often, usually around Christmas, B&BW will release limited editions of their signature scents as parfum. These are slightly different, as they're interpretations of the original fragrance (a kind of sheer floral oriental with a musky vanilla base that is really something). The red glass bottle with black vines (Bath & Body Works Signature Collection Couture Limited Edition No. 3 Eau de Parfum Japanese Cherry Blossom) is heavier on the musky side, and lighter on the vanilla, and the vanilla isn't very sweet... so you get this very sexy, very warm fragrance that seems to kind of float in the air around you. Later versions (like the Ruby Red bottle, a red glass disc with gold Asian design) are sweeter and more vanilla focused; Still lovely, still fantastic, but not as dark and sexy as No. 3.

As I write this review, there are 2 bottles for sale on Amazon starting at $150 each. I would love to buy them, but my husband would kill me for spending that much on something with an original price of $29. Sigh. But straight up, it's worth it.

column6: EM-3513W Sleep Mask
column13: Best sleep mask I’ve tried so far
column14:
I’ve been using an eye mask for sleeping for many years and know a great deal about what features I find necessary in order to get a good night’s sleep. I could see from the description that this mask by Drift To Sleep had all the features I required. As a result, I was eager to try it when the manufacturer contacted me offering a free sample in exchange for an honest review. Over the last five years, I’ve reviewed many different types and brands of eye masks, but I’ve always reverted back to using masks that have at least these four essential features:

• It’s constructed of lightweight molded foam covered on the outside with a poly fabric;
• The foam contains large eyecups so my eyelids can blink or move (in REM sleep) without touching any part of the mask;
• The foam contains a cutout for the bridge of my nose so no light can seep in around my nose;
• It has an adjustable approximately three-quarter-inch-wide elastic strap.

Without these four features, a mask will not work ideally for me to keep the light out and make me (mostly) forget that I’m wearing a sleep mask. Before I discovered that I needed these four features, I’d tried just about all the different type of eye masks there are. I probably have over two-dozen unused eye masks in my bedside table.

What I like about this Drift To Sleep mask more than the current mask I was using (that one was a Good Night Sleep Mask purchased from Magellan’s, the travel goods company) is that this mask has a slightly thinner profile of foam around the eyecups. The eyecups are the same size on both brands, but the Drift To Sleep mask has a slightly slimmer frame of foam all around. As a result, there is less foam actually resting on my forehead and cheeks. It might seem like a small thing, but it makes a big difference, especially in the hot weather when the eye mask can become a bit too warm and actually cause the skin under the mask to sweat. The Drift To Sleep mask has the same advantage in the bridge-of-the-nose cutout. i.e., it is less bulky than the Magellan’s brand nose cup. Both shut the light out, but the Drift To Sleep mask shuts out the light with less foam touching the skin and therefore is more comfortable in warm weather.

This is definitely the best sleep mask I’ve tried so far! I plan to use it from now on...unless, of course, I find another that I like even better. I’m hoping that some manufacturer will come up with flexible molded-eye-and-nose-pockets product that is lightweight and will allow for air circulation against the skin on hot nights.

I know from past experience with these types of masks can occasionally be washed by hand and reused for at least 12 to 18 months. By then, you’ll probably want to get a new one because the foam will start to get old (and full of dead skin and face oils despite the washing) and the adhesive holding the fabric covering in place may have worn off in spots. Nothing lasts forever under daily use and to get one to two years out of an item like this seems appropriate to me. Silk eye masks can last a long time and they are very cool in summer, but they have no eyecups, which are essential.

This sleep mask would make a nice small gift for any group holiday gift exchange party. In particular, it’s a nice idea to give the gift of a good night’s sleep; it is a gift that people will remember; and it comes in a lovely box that needs nothing but a bow to make it special.ame advantage in the bridge-of-the-nose cutout. i.e., it is less bulky than the Magellan’s brand nose cup. column6: Wahl Clipper Elite Pro High Performance Haircut Kit for men with Hair Clippers, Secure fit guide combs with stainless steel clips By The Brand used by Professionals. #79602
column14:
Bought this at a store in person. First, out of all the brands at varying prices that ive owned, id say by far that i personally think Wahl is the best.

As for this elite pro model in particular, i am very impressed. Its motor seems much stronger than other models, it cuts through my hair with little effort and no snagging. Other clippers ive had would snag my hair or my hair would pass through without being cut (i have straight thin hair).
I do like the metal tab at the back of the attachments since it seems to hold onto the clipper better than the plain plastic style, but i do not like that it does NOT include tapered ear attachments as ive used those with previous models to help give the area around my ears a cleaner look.

From experience in owning a few of these just a tip, do not ever use any oil to lubricate the blades other than oil made specifically for hair clippers. Also, do not apply the oil directly from the bottle to the blades. The oil bottle comes sealed in a little bag with a small black brush, put just one or two drops of oil onto that brush and then brush the oil onto the blades with the clipper OFF, youre looking for just a very light coating. Then turn on the clipper and let it run for a few seconds with no attachments on it to help the oil lubricate the blades more evenly.

column6: Hyaluronic Acid Vitamin C Serum Natural Skin Care Products. Anti Aging Moisturizer for Healthy Skin with Vitamin E Oil, Lavender Oil. Paraben Free Timeless Formula
column14:
I'm familiar with hyaluronic acid, because I've used several different brands in the past. As a woman in my early thirties, I'm very focused on skincare, and I can vouch that hyaluronic acid is a GREAT addition to anyone's facial ritual. This is definitely one of the best brands I've used.

The way I apply it is first I was my face with cetaphil cleanser, next I apply a layer of this serum and let it soak in, then I finish with my nighttime moisturizer (I only use HA serum at night, personal choice). Using it this way, HA evens out my skin tone and seems to work with the moisturizer, keeping my skin soft all day, and negating any dryness WITHOUT feeling greasy or oily. Please note that this particular product has aloe in it, so I've found that it goes on a little sticky, which can be disconcerting. No worries, though, just wait for your skin to soak it up, and all is well.

My order also came with a sample of the most delicious smelling cleanser I've ever come across in my life (I'm being serious). I'll probably end up ordering some in full size.

(I received this serum at a discount, in exchange for my opinion and honest review of the product.)
