column14:
Prime Organix Anti Aging Moisturizer is simply my favorite moisturizer I have tried recently. It leaves my face amazingly soft and not greasy. I am very picky when it comes to skin care. I can't stand anything that makes my skin greasy or sticky. This was creamy and rubs in great with a nice smooth soft finish.
I also love the packaging it comes in. I hate when creams are in tubes or bottles that you have to struggle to get the product from. Prime organix comes in a pump type bottle that guarantees you will get all of the product out without the waste.
Prime Organix has a subtle scent that isn't very noticeable at first. I really like that since some scents tend to bother my skin. While I don't typically use a moisturizer daily since my skin type is on the oilier side, I have been using it daily in the summer since I am at the pool a lot and the sun and chlorine tend to dry out my face more. So I have been applying it at bedtime so that it can stay on my face overnight and help hydrate the sun damage. It seems to be working well. It leaves my face nice and soft the next morning.

column6: Golden Sundrops Royal Jelly Antiaging Night Cream (1.5oz / 42g) Hyaluronic Acid Vitamin A and E Rose Hip Oil Kokum Butter Skin Healing Dry Skin Face Neck Moisturize Decrease Fine Lines Reduce Wrinkles
column14:
I'd like to start by saying I love this face cream. I'm on my second jar. It is too greasy to use for daytime, but it is labeled as night cream, so I was expecting that (and I wanted a night cream).

However, the consistency is not the same between jar 1 and jar 2. The first jar was more greasy/oily cream, which I loved. It wasn't greasy on my pillow case, and by morning it soaked up into my skin perfectly. The second jar I received had a more creamy consistency--still the same night cream, I don't question that.. but it seemed thicker, less oily. When I put it on it feels like it takes longer to sink in, and it sits there more mask like. I feel like the second jar works okay, but the first jar worked better for me. I saw better results with the first.

I'm almost done with my 2nd jar, so we'll see what the third jar ends up like.
This night cream really plumps up the skin, hydrates, and gives a phenomenal glow! It doesn't cause breakouts, and doesn't leave a greasy mess on my pillow case. If I skip using it for even 2-3 days, I can immediately see the difference in my skin's appearance and go back to using it. It also doesn't have a heavy scent, which is nice.. a light one-yes, but not perfume scent, just a natural slightly honey like scent.

column6: Hair Removal Waxing Kit Men + Women, All Natural | BodyHonee (10 Oz)
column13: Works great.  Like a lot more than the standard waxing kits.
column14:
I just started waxing this past year and had been using the standard wax hair removal kits sold in the drug stores. Decided to give sugar wax a try and am so glad I did. I love this stuff! I use it on my underarms and lower legs, and it works very well. For the actual hair removal, I'd say it works about the same as the regular wax kits I had been using (the stuff you melt in the tub, not the strips), but I love this so much more because it is so ridiculously easy to use and clean up. It's water-soluble, so any residue just easily washes/wipes away, and it's not drippy sticky like glue the way the regular wax is.

You only get two wooden sticks with this kit and that's plenty because after you use one, you just run it under water to clean it for next time. I bought a package of JMT Beauty Non-woven Waxing Strips to make sure I have plenty of strips on hand, and I'd recommend them as well. They work perfectly with this sugar wax. These are the products I plan to continue using for hair removal.

column6: A Softer Baby Foot Peel & Foot Mask to Exfoliate Feet, Repair Rough Heels, Peeling Away Dry Dead Skin, Callus Remover Treatment, Smooth Cracked Heels Pack with Two Foot Cream & Lotion Scrub Socks!
column13: I was amazed at the amount of peeling!
column14: After a couple days of using this product as recommended, my feet started to peel, and continued to do so for the next 5 days. I was amazed at the amount of skin that came off. My skin even peeled between my toes and on top of my feet! By day 6 I still had a little peeling, but had softer, smoother feet. Before I did this peel, I was in  need of a pedicure, but not anymore! This is so much more convenient to do at home, and the results were actually way better than what I've gotten from salon pedicures. Just a few tips: When you apply the socks for the 60-90 minutes, make sure to put a pair of your own socks over them if you plan on getting up and walking around, because they are a little slippery. Also on about the second day my feet felt pretty dry, but resist the urge to apply lotion or oils so the peeling process can start. Also when you apply the prefilled socks, it helps a little to massage your feet so that the product can really soak in. I think this is a great product and I'm really impressed how much softer my skin is, just be patient because the peeling action doesn't really start until usually the third or fourth day. I did receive this item for free however all opinions are 100% my own.

column6: Braun Silk-épil 7 Wet and Dry Epilator, White
column14: When I received this product,  I was very excited to try it.  When I opened the box,  I got even more excited when I realized that it has a built-in light and the speed setting(two speed setting)  is very easy  to control.  I like how It clicks to the next speed,  instead of those slide buttons. It has 5 attachment heads,  a bag and a brush that is in perfect size to clean the attachment heads.  The attachment heads are supposed to help prevent broken skin and make the epilating experience less painful and intimidating. Each attachment head is for certain parts of the body; so before using this epilator,  be sure to read the manual carefully.This epilator is rechargeable which is great if your going away for the weekend and you want to pack light!  Now,  I have already tried it to remove facial hair,  leg hair and armpit hair, and let me tell you,  this is the best epilator I have ever used! When I used it on my face,  it definitely got rid of my mustache! (not that,  it was a lot,  but I get very conscious about it.  And the hair wasn't even long,  I can barely see it!) it left the top of my upper lip red but not irritated for only a few minutes. (I was actually worried that it was gonna stay red until the next day because I have very sensitive skin). The next day,  I used it on my leg using the attachment  that is specifically for the epilating the legs. I had to go really slow and against the hair growth because my leg hair isn't really that long. (leg hair and armpit hair needs to be at least,  half a centimeter to achieve best results.) it didn't really hurt,  the attachment head makes it less intimidating to use the epilator. Then I tried it on my armpit,  and Lo and behold! No broken skin! No bleeding,  no skin irritation,  not even any sign of redness!  I was very impressed!  I gave it a four star because the manual,  in my own opinion isn't very user friendly.  The drawings for the attachment heads are a little confusing.  I also had to read the manual every time I had to change the attachment head,  which to me is a little annoying,  but it was worth it! Overall,  this is a great epilator! Probably,  one of the best in the market! It's great for someone who will be using an epilator for the first time!

column6: MapofBeauty Fashion Beautyful Long Straight 7 Pieces Full Head Set Hair Extensions
column14: I've never used extensions before so wasn't sure what to expect. I had a hard time finding some to match my hair color. I have natural medium brown hair with a little red hue to it, and I have high lights of medium to light blonde done monthly with low lights every other month. I looked a long time for extensions that best matches my highlight color but they all looked either too chunky, too light, or too dark. I had my hair darkened a lite last time and when I ran across these extensions, they looked like they would match the best out of all the ones I've seen that weren't priced too high. I bought them for $7 and it said they would arrive in almost two months so I was pleasantly surprised to have them arrive after two weeks! They were very VERY long-- I had to cut a lot off because my hair is fairly short (barely shoulder length) and the length difference was ridiculous. Down side is the hair is almost like Barbie doll hair-- it's really shiny. And it doesn't curl AT ALL, major bummer because I think curling extensions make them blend better. No weird smell though. Also came already on the clips. One pack was a little thin for my liking but it's working for now. I'm gonna order another pack. The color wasn't a perfect match but close enough. For a first time user I was pretty pleased but they tangle super easily and they shed when your brush or comb them out to be careful not to play with them while they're in. All in all worth the money and will buy again as well as recommend to others. Included before/after pics.

column6: Vitamin C Lotion - Natural Face Moisturizer - POWERFUL Antioxidants Vitamin C & Green Tea - Hydrating Jojoba Oil, Shea Butter - Restoring Panthenol & MSM - Foxbrim 3.4OZ
column14:
As a product tester I compare dozens of skin care products, and I've arrived at a list of key considerations from fragrance to long-term results. I hope these are helpful to you!

~ Fragrance: Very faint, lotiony
~ Color and texture: White, medium to thick lotion
~ Feel during application: Smooth and thick, spreads nicely
~ Feel after absorption: Moister, cool, not oily or sticky
~ Is it best for a certain skin type?: Fine for all. Not sure I would use it on an oily face.
~ Is it tested on animals?: No
~ Packaging: 1.7oz white plastic pump bottle. Pump offers reasonably good control.
~ Immediate cosmetic effects:* Dry skin looks moistened.
~ Potential long-term effectiveness:* Definitely better than using an ordinary lotion without active ingredients. MSM, vitamin C, and vitamin B5 are good things to have. The moisturizing oils are palm oil, safflower oil, shea butter, and jojoba oil. The formula isn't anything to write home about but it's good for your skin.
~ Other notes: This listing on amazon is for 3.4oz; I got half that, a 1.7oz container. At 1.7oz this is priced like a treatment cream that should have a lot more in terms of active ingredients, but it's more like a moisture lotion with a few extras. If I'd actually gotten the amount advertised, I would consider this a four-star product because the price would be more in line with what you get. Instead, it's a poor value and false advertising.

*Know the difference between cosmetic and long-term effects: Cosmetic effects are immediate and only present when the product has been applied recently - just like makeup. Long-term effects take longer to see and should remain when you stop using the product (but don't when you find something effective - your skin needs continuing support). The ideal product would be both cosmetically and long-term effective, but it's more realistic to expect a formula to tilt towards one or the other.

column6: Braun Series 9 9090cc Men's Electric Foil Shaver / Electric Razor with Cleansing Center, Razors, Shavers, & Cordless Shaving System
column14:
Edit: I tried this product as part of a promotional campaign. Here's my two cents:

The Good: I have almost always used the traditional rotary electric razors, which I had found gave me a better, closer shave. I was wary about the special foils and the 4-way shaving system; it seemed at first too much like another Gillette-esque gimmick. However, after shaving several times with the Braun Series 9, I must confess that I have found that not only does it truly pick up those difficult hairs on the first pass, it also excels in reaching those difficult areas like the chin and neck; this is a big deal for me! Also, the foils are easily removed for quick cleaning, and the trimmer mechanism is clean and convenient.

The Neutral: The cleaning station. While a neat feature (essentially what it does is bathe the foils in an alcohol solution for cleaning and disinfecting) it's not something I would pay the extra bucks for--a quick rinse every so often has always worked great for me. As long as I'm the only one using it, I don't feel a need for deep cleaning.

The Bad: The Braun Series 9 is not travel size. It is certainly the largest electric shaver I've ever owned--it does come with a nice zip up travel case though. If you plan on using it exclusively at home, this is obviously not an issue. Also, the lock for adjusting the head angle is right at the spot where you put your thumb when you hold it, and it too easily comes unlocked while you shave, allowing the head to move around too much.

column14:
The Lavender with Rosemary Extract Shampoo has a wonderful scent that leaves my hair shiny, soft and moisturized. I love that it's an all natural herbal shampoo that doesn't contain parabens, or sulfates. I have never in my life seen a bottle of shampoo that contained such simple ingredients including coconut oil, lavender, rosemary, sage, rose petal, aloe and calendula extracts, organic honey, soya protein and DM water... Nothing else!!

I received 4 bottles of Vaadi Shampoo each weighing almost 4oz (3.87oz). They don't take up valuable space in my shower and are easy to travel with. I have included product pictures for reference.

Two years ago I had highlights that fried my hair. My once thick, long, glorious head of hair has since fallen out and thinned leaving me with a disaster in comparison. Since I've started using my Lavender Rosemary Shampoo I'm noticing a new shine and more moisture in my hair. It has become easier to manage and feel healthier, not to mention my hair smells amazing!!

The lather is rich, although not as rich as shampoos full of chemicals... It's the chemicals that make a soapy lather. For a natural shampoo it has exceeded my expectations. It leaves my hair feeling naturally clean and the shampoo is gentle enough to use on my children. I appreciate being able to pronounce the ingredients and that they are ingredients I am familiar with. Disclaimer: I received this product at no cost in exchange for my honest, unbiased review. Regardless, I'm very pleased with the overall quality and the results I'm seeing with the Vaadi Lavender Rosemary Shampoo and would happily purchase.

column14:

My skin has changed over the course of the years, from dry to oily (depending on seasons and life changes) but this Rose Petal Witch Hazel has always made my skin feel squeaky clean and soft.

column6: Baby Foot Exfoliant Foot Peel, Lavender Scented, 2.4 Fl. Oz.
column13: Does it really work as well as they say? Absolutely!
column14:
My feet were horrible. I love to go barefoot any time I can and you could tell. My heels were dry, cracked deeply, sore to walk on and the skin was so hard that I barely had any feeling in them. I had to rub my feet in coconut oil any time I went out in public because the dry, cracked skin was so embarrassing. Lotions, creams, files, lavender oil - nothing hid the damage for more than an hour or two. Baby Foot has made my feet look BRAND NEW.

- I did soak before using it & soak for 15 minutes every day after. No lotions or oils.
- Day 1 - 3 my feet just looked dry - the skin looked kind of like tissue paper, worse than usual. I was scared I'd ruined them. But on day 4 the peeling started. Small patches at first, but the more I soaked - the more skin fell off.
- You WILL have a lot of dead skin to deal with. It will go everywhere! I wore socks at all times so I didn't leave a trail of skin around the house.
- The tops of my feet & ankles did peel, but not until the last 2 days.
- By day 11 I was finished and I have never been happier! No more cracks, my heels are soft and pink again. Even my toes look better.
- There are a few small areas that could use a bit more help because they still FEEL a little rough even though they look great, so I may do a second application in a few weeks.

This product is fantastic!! I've been telling all my friends about it.

column6: Kirkland Signature Minoxidil Foam for Men, 12.6 oz
column13: Im giving it 4 stars because anything that requires daily use sucks, but
column14:
Okay, This stuff does work.. Im giving it 4 stars because anything that requires daily use sucks, but, you gotta do what you gotta do...I prefer this minoxidil over the liquid brand because it does not contain propylene glycol... Propylene Glycol makes my scalp itch, alot.. So the liquid version seems to do more damage than good.. Some people complain about the foams inability to make contact with the scalp, I have a little trick for you guys.. Fill up a cup of hot water, fill the minoxidil cap halfway with the foam, submerse the cap in the water, not to the point where water fills the cap.. After about 20 seconds the foam will liquify, then use a medicine dropper to apply the minoxidil directly to the scalp... :)

Now onto the reason why this product does not work for some people.. Minoxidil is not a hair loss product, it is a hair growth product! It's actual mechanism of action is to "open channels" in the scalp allowing more blood and oxygen to the follicle... Thats all it does.. If you have a terrible diet and live a terrible life, this product will send "terrible" blood to your scalp.. Making your hairloss worse...

So, before you decide to use any type of minoxidil you should take a good hard look at you diet and lifestyle.. Excessive alcohol consumption, cigarette smoking, fast food and a sedentary lifestyle will typically make this product ineffective..

Some helpful hints to make this product more effective...
limit alcohol consumption to once a week..
smoke cigarettes only when you drink..
adopt a paleo diet..
take a zinc supplement, 50 mg a day works for me..
use a ketoconazole shampoo a few times a week..
a multivitamin will help, just don't overdo it.. Less is more when it comes to multivitamins..
get some exercise, it will help cleanse your body of all the crap..

Once you fix the "inside" you can fix the "outside".. Hope this info helps.. Good luck!lps.. Good luck!

column6: Lactic Acid 50% Gel Peel 1 oz - Enhanced with Kojic Acid & Bearberry Extract
column14:
The instructions in the box are detailed but still required some internet research to clarify things that were not easily understood.

I started with the lowest dosage as instructed, 2 weeks later did the next step, 2 weeks later, did the next, etc until 10 weeks later I was at full strength. During the first 4 applications I was fine. My face was a little red when I washed it off but quickly faded. With the 5th application, which was the fullest strength, it burned my face and I had marks and severe redness for a week. I had no idea it was burning my face because it didn't give a burning feeling. When I removed it with the water, I discovered the burn marks. The following morning my face was in pain.

I hopped online to find a quick remedy and had already had a lotion that was suggested for burns. I used that along with some vitamin E and lavender oil (which is a antiseptic and promotes skin rejuvenation) to keep my face moisturized enough to keep from blistering. Luckily a few days into it I happened to have a doctors appointment and she ended up giving me a prescription cream that is for fading scars, which was why I was using the peel. I discovered the cream was also good for burns so I continued using that and within 3 more days I was healed up.

In that 10 weeks of applications I didn't see any difference in my marks, or my skin appearance in general. I know it takes a while to work show a difference but considering the 5 times I used it used about half the bottle, the money wasn't worth it. The cream I have been using was about the same price (not covered by my insurance). I have been using twice a day for 2 weeks, with no side effects and have already noticed significant fading of my scars. I think I will stick with the cream and avoid the possibility of more burning.

I am rating at "I don't like it" instead of "I hate it" because I have seen reviews where it has worked wonders for others. It's just not for me.

column6: RHX 6 pcs Nail Art Pens Brushes 3 Fine Drawing 3 Striping Liner Design Set Nail Tips
column14:
I have been using these nail brushes for a few months now. They work well. The three longer ones are made of a hollow plastic, so they are very light. I prefer a heavier brush so I simply added alittle molding clay just above the brush at the metal part.
The red ended (NO.1) brush is 6 3/4" long w/ the bristles, The bristles are 1/2" long. The green ended (NO.2) brush is 7" long w/the bristles, the bristles are 3/4" long. And the blue ended (NO.3) brush is 7" long w/bristles, the bristles are 1" in length.
These 1, 2 & 3 brushes are strip brushes. For making lines, feathers whatever comes to mind with these brushes.
The other three have wooden handles. Two measuring 5 1/2" long, w/bristles, the bristles are 1/2" long & 1/4" long. The third brush w/bristles is 5 1/4" long , the bristlesare 1/16" long.
These three brushes I use for flowers, clouds, grass , these short bristles could paint many things on your nails. I paint birds, trees , leaves. These brushes are small yet big in punch. They hold nail polishes & acrylic paints very well, and are really easy to clean. I haven't lost any bristles from them either.
They came with clear plastic open ended covers , but they don't stay on very well, unless firmly pushing them down onto the handles. I just don't use them, I store my nail brushes in a vinyl baggie, open end so they get air. Bristles face up.
These brushes haven't disappointed me so far.
'THANKS FOR READING, '

column6: ARM & HAMMER Truly Radiant Battery Toothbrush + Toothpaste Pack
column13: A bit too powerful and intense for me
column14:
I have always wanted to try an electric toothbrush, and my seven-year-old daughter loves her Monster High one. Unfortunately, I found this to be too powerful for me, which can be good if you want a daily cleaning like you're at your dentist's office. But for me, I don't like holding objects for long that have strong, intense vibrations, and two minutes can seem like a lifetime when something is uncomfortable.

Despite the top brushes of the head being bent somewhat due to shipping (the plastic was pushed in), the brush itself was comfortable, and easy to remove for replacing. I can't say the same for the battery compartment, which says to turn and pull, but it's hard to turn a rectangular piece. The batteries themselves seemed slick, which makes me wonder how secure the compartment is from moisture, and worries me that the brush won't last long.

The tootpaste itself tastes more like baking soda than mint, but at least it leaves the mouth feeling clean. Overall, I was not as thrilled with this as I hoped. If you are well used to electric toothbrushes or intense, rough cleanings, you'll likely have a better experience. For me, though, it was a little too much.

I have used it 3 times now and have had minimal fade in my bright purple hair. I might actually be able to go 5 more extra days without coloring it again because the fadding in my hair color is minimal.

My hair is soft, bouncy, lightweight and shiney. Not to mention the shampoo and conditioner smell sublime. Even my husband walked up to me and sniffed my head and said, "wow your hair smells really good!" I guess he kept walking past me and couldn't figure out if I was wearing a new lotion or perfume and was shocked that it was the shampoo and conditioner I used.

I would highly reccomend this product to anyone who colors their hair ANY color, weather your color is Natural or a Fun color. One thing I did notice is it takes a little more shampoo or product to use in your hair. The shampoo and conditioner instantly absorb into your wet hair, so to get a good lather note that you will need a little more shampoo than you normally use. The conditioner is great too, it does not feel greasy so I added a little extra in my hair as well because without that traditional greasy feeling I was not sure if I added enough. So i again used a little more than I normally do. After I dried my hair, it felt as good as the Kevin Murphy and other expensive products my hair stylist uses.

I am definitely going to purchase more in the future. Great packaging and fast shipping!

column6: Kyoku For Men Exfoliating Facial Scrub | Kyoku For Men Face Scrub, A Gentle Acne Treatment For Men (3.4oz)
column14:
Originally it was purchased for my hubby but I decided what the heck I will give it a go. I have used numerous kinds of acne face wash and nothing really seemed to help. ProActive was good while it lasted, but after about 2 months the acne seemed to evolve and again I was breaking out constantly. The other ones I have tried are your basic drug store brands so I won't bother to go into much detail on those.

Now this stuff. I wanted to give it a full 5 stars but overall it doesn't combat my acne fully (it does do a decent job, though). What it does do, however, is make my skin softer, more radiant and it is minimizing my pores. Heck, I even just bought their pore minimizing serum so we'll see how that goes. This face wash feels so good when you put it on. The little bean exfoliate beads inside of it really do their job and if you rub softly they don't irritate your skin at all (so if you want to really grind up your skin, just rub hard.).

Letting it sit for the full minute is hit or miss. It is pretty strong in comparison to other face washes. The first time I let it sit the tops of my apple cheeks started to burn and I got a-scurred and quickly washed it off. The second time, a few days later, was much better but still it starts to really make your skin feel icy-burny shortly into sitting. I really like the feeling though, and I think it only irritated my skin because of how large my pores were at the time.

My hubby likes it and his skin looks pretty dang clear, much more so than mine. It smells good and I like how easily it goes on. It doesn't foam up (much?) and sits nicely on your face. I could say it is comparable to St. Ive's Exfoliate face washes, but more creamy. It also seems to penetrate deeper thus giving you a better clean.

Now keep in mind your face will be tight after using this. Not much of an expert on facey-things but I assume this is one of those face washes you need a moisturizer after. I suggest a light essential oil type as they are less greasy than creams.

So in a nutshell this is a 4.5 out of 5 product for me. If my acne condition improves I will up it to a full 5 stars. My hubby on the other hand, would give it a full 5.ssential oil type as they are less greasy than creams.

So in a nutshell this is a 4.5 out of 5 product for me. If my acne condition improves I will up it to a full 5 stars. My hubby on the other hand, would give it a full 5.

column14:
It is tough to find a good natural deodorant. So, I am basing this rating on comparisons to other natural deodorants, not "unnatural" deodorants. I'm doing this because there just isn't a comparison between natural brands and other brands. Natural brands just don't work as well.

So, with that said, Herban Cowboy is my favorite. I've found that it requires less applications Han other natural deodorants. It also smells much better. I've found other natural deodorants tend to smell like body odor mixed with natural scents... It's just weird. Herban Cowboy does not do this. It retains a good scent, so long as you reapply often.

Even though I do like this brand, I no longer wear any deodorants. Although, I do keep a stick of this in my closet just in case.

column13: My hair looks so beautiful, the jet black hair is gone
column14: I just want to really really let everyone know that color oops actually works!!! I think what is important is not to wait longer than 72 hours to put the product on and to actually take the time to follow the directions.

column6: Sandalwood Natural Soap Bar with Shea Butter 5oz
column13: It's Soap: I Wasn't Expecting Much ... But I Was Pleasantly Surprised!
column14:
Gotta be honest: as a guy – a traditional, middle class red-blooded male – there are things in life I just take for granted. For example, soap is soap is soap. Right? I mean, sure, there are different brands with different cleaning formulas and different names and ingredients, right? You get in the shower, and you reach for whatever bar is there, and you wash yourself off, but it’s honestly a product I haven’t invested all that much time, effort, and thought into.

So when I was asked to review a bar from Soap.Club, I really didn’t quite know what to expect. I mean I knew my world probably wasn’t going to be rocked, and I figured the Heavens weren’t going to fall down around my ankles. Like I said above, it’s soap … right? How different can it be from the last soap I used? (Again, you’ll have to pardon my man-ness.)

Still, this Sandalwood Soother surprised me. Right out of the box, I sniffed it, and I honestly didn’t much notice a scent or an odor all that different from the soap I had used the day before. You know what I mean? It has that soapy, clean smell but there’s a hint of something more in there. My nose perhaps isn’t as learned enough as the next to notice any significant difference … but it wasn’t until actually using it for a few days in the shower that I started to appreciate what Soap.Club’s product is all about.

The bar actually lathers up quite nicely, giving off a wonderful head of bubbles; and the feel of the soap on my arms and whatnot was a touch more like the good oils used by my licensed massage therapist. As for the sandalwood scent, it’s definitely not anything overpowering, but it’s strong enough to hang on to the skin with a pronounced hint after drying off. Certainly, that’s a nice extra as I live in the Great American Southwest where temperatures just yesterday were 117 … so any extra deodorizing effect from any product is greatly appreciated.

Perhaps the greatest aftereffect to using this bar from Soap.Club I experienced is that – unlike many store-bought alternatives – my skin doesn’t feel dry or cracked or tight once I’ve sponged off the water and even an hour or so after cleaning. My experience is that many soaps have a tendency to dry out the skin, giving me that kinda/sorta parched feeling as the day wears on, but that definitely isn’t the case with this Sandalwood bar.

So I’ll definitely keep using this, and – when it’s done – I’ll quite possibly be picking up another one so long as my skin continues to feel the way it does in the weeks ahead. Watch this space, and I’ll update should it become necessary.

Highly recommended. Gotta be honest: it isn’t all that often I get excited over personal hygiene products of this nature (I honestly haven’t reviewed all that many, and – as a man – I probably tend like most to take certain things for granted when it comes to cleaning up), but I loved the quality and fragrance of this Sandalwood Soother from Soap.Club.

column6: Cover-Dot Acne Care - Clear Acne Absorbing Patch
column13: Keeps me from picking at acne, & reduces scarring
column14:
UPDATE:
I've updated my rating from 3 stars to 5, because I really hate to be without these things now - I'll panic a little if I forget to bring them on trips away from home. No, they still don't heal acne, but if I've expressed a pimple (because I can't stop myself), these hydrocolloid dots provide a moist healing environment. My picked-at pimple will heal faster and won't get a dry scab, reducing any scarring. I get acne on my chest and shoulders in the summer for some reason, and these dots help hide the red blemish, and they blend in well. They work great on most of my face and for the most part aren't very noticeable, but I will say that near my chin and mouth where my skin has a lot of movement from me talking and smiling, the dots will wrinkle at the edges, making them very noticeable, so do keep that in mind.

I did try the Nexcare brand of acne dots, and those have raised edges that are noticeable, and they also don't stay on well at all - each morning I'd wake up to find the acne dot had come off and was somewhere in the bedsheets or had restuck onto me elsewhere. These Cover-Dots don't have that problem at all, they stay on for 48 hours or more. Very happy with these Cover-Dots from SMARTMED.

ORIGINAL REVIEW:
Do these dots make my acne disappear? No. I can wear these for 24 hours and they stay in place despite my oily skin, but they don't make my acne go away, or suck out pus from an unpopped zit (ew, sorry I'm mentioning it) or anything. If a zit has been popped it does help the area stay clean so I'm not dabbing with a tissue every 2 minutes, and helps it heal that way. It also keeps me from picking at acne (which is a big problem for me) which is the main reason I use these.

It's best to remove them after washing your face with warm water, it helps loosen the adhesive of the dot. I don't have any experience trying to cover these with makeup, as I just wear them around the house.

So, an "acne cure"? Not for me. But it keeps me from picking at my face and that's a good thing (I'm my own worst enemy).rom picking at my face and that's a good thing (I'm my own worst enemy).

column6: Spenco PolySorb Earthbound Insoles
column14:
I bought these after trying on a number of insoles in the store, to fit within sneakers used primarily to play Squash. Since there is really no way to know how they'll feel in real use, I figured why not go more material-conscious if they feel more/less equivalent in the store.

After just a few uses, I started to feel pain and some bruising in the inner metatarsal (big inner) bone. After a while, I estimated that the angle of the pad created too much additional stress toward the front, as the back have very thick cushion and very little at the front (which seems not to be uncommon with 'athletic' innersoles). So I had to remove them after limited use, and have noticed the inflammation subside.

I can't say this will happen to everyone's feet of course -- and the review is for strenuous use with a lot of forceful striding -- but for me these innersoles were a counterproductive expenditure of money.

column14: [[VIDEOID:9bcd628ec921d1ae9ce03257c1d2de63]]I have a genetic condition that makes me grow hairs on my neck and chin and it's so embarrassing. I usually tweezers them but it takes forever. This epilator hurts as much as tweezers but the difference is that it is faster. It saves time and it is like ripping a bandaid off quickly, way more tolerable than the painstakingly slow alternative. It comes with 2 different heads, one for smaller areas like underarms and one for larger areas like legs. I personally don't like shaving because my hair grows back the next day. By pulling the root of the hairs out, this last much longer  (2-4 weeks). It comes with a cooling spray that I really liked. This isn't loud, my husband could hear it right outside the bathroom door but not much farther. I like that it is a plug in item instead of battery ran because I usually can't find a battery to save my life. My husband likes to hoard the batteries for his game controllers lol. It also has 2 speeds and is super easy to clean. After using this epilator, my skin was a little irritated and red. It goes away on its own in about a day but I would suggest putting lotion or aloe vera on it. For longer hairs, you'd have to trim them down before you use it. Likewise, you cannot use this on super short hair because the epilator cannot grab the hair. Overall I'm thankful for this product making my life do much easier. I have added a video of my review so you can see this baby in action! I received this product at a discounted price in exchange for my honest review.

column14: I purchased this razor as I was looking for an alternative to my Merkur Futur razor. Don't get me wrong I like the Merkur Futur I have had it for 6yrs now and its still going strong but I was looking for something a little bit lighter which the R89 Twist is by about 1oz  (120gm vs 90gm) and I was looking for a thinner head so that I can maneuver the razor around the bottom of my nose mustache area easier which this razor does very well. I like the adjustability of the Futur but have come to the conclusion that having an adjustable razor it is not necessary unless you have particular skin issues, etc which require you to adjust the razor to avoid aggravating your skin. This razor is not adjustable, but seems setup to give a close non-aggressive shave which I like, and the handle has a good diameter, and is knurled to give you a positive grip.  The razor feels very well balanced in the hand. The quality of the razor seems great the twist mechanism is precise, no rattle in the handle or head, the lockup of head to handle and blade alignment are perfect. column6: Evening Primrose Carrier Oil. A Base Oil for Aromatherapy, Essential Oil or Massage use.
column14:
As a sufferer of eczema I have heard nothing but wonderful things about Evening Primrose Oil. I have a few other products from Plant Therapy so I thought it would be the perfect brand to get the Evening Primrose oil from. I have had this oil for about 5 days now and I have found wonderful things to do with it besides helping with my eczema. This Plant Therapy Evening Primrose Oil comes in a plastic bottle with a snap lid. It is a nice size bottle with 4 ounces of product.

Evening Primrose oil is the oil from the seed of the evening primrose plant. Evening Primrose Oil is a carrier oil so it can be used alone directly onto the skin or essential oils can be added to it to enhance its versatility. After a shower I use the primrose oil with a few drops of tea tree oil as well. This combination is very soothing to my dry, sometimes red, patchy skin. This mixture could also be used on the hair to combat dandruff. The primrose and tea tree oil does wonders for my eczema and even only after a few days I am noticing that my skin is not as dry. I will continue on with this regimen and hope that it works well into the winter when my skin gets hit the most because of the weather. This a good product and I am happy that I decided to try it.

I have received a discount on this product in exchange for my honest and unbiased review. I enjoy writing reviews and put a lot of effort into how I feel about the products. I think it is important as consumers to make a well informed decision before purchasing a product.

Because of the hole in the ozone layer and the cruel rays of the sun our skin is very susceptible to all sorts of happenings..dark spots, age spots, freckles, melasma and hyperpigmentati.  Whether we are women or men our skin is the same and the sun does what it does regardless of who we are!  Yes, i am vain about my looks so i checked out some of the products that can be used to help correct the effects of the sun and came across a small family run business  called Protege (i am not a fan of big companies at all!) who are in Blaine, Washington.  I purchased their product called Luminate and am amazed at how it has lightened my skin and got rid of the dark spots on my hands and  chest and pigmentation at the side of my face.    I just wanted to share this with you in case you too are as particular as I am about your looks...and I know there are many beautiful women and men who are my friends.    Their website site is:[...]  and their products available also on Amazon.com

column6: Facial Serum and Cream Kit by Ageless La Cure - Natural, Organic, Hydrating, Lifting and Toning by Phyto 5, 1.5 Ounce
column14: Update:    I took photos before commencing this trial, and photos after using the this kit for two weeks.  I used photos to try to limit the placebo effect and make the comparison more objective.  I see no discernible difference between the before and after photos.    Original review:  This serum and cream duo are advertised as anti-aging.  For the price you pay, you get 1 Tablespoon of the serum and 2 Tablespoons of the cream.  For the price, I would expect it to be more than just a moisturizer.  I have used many, many less expensive anti-aging moisturizers, because like everyone else would rather look 25 than decades older.  However, as one dermatologist said, "none of these products actually works" or she (50-ish) would look 22, which of course she didn't.  The product comes in an elegant box with two pump bottles, and a pamphlet.  The pamphlet instructs you how to massage your face.  There are no instructions on how to use the product, but on the Amazon site there is further information.  You are supposed to use the cream in the morning.  In the evening, use the serum, followed by the cream.  The Phyto 5 serum is said to "fill wrinkles from the inside" and to "provide restoration, protection and much needed hydration."  The cream is said to be "rich in anti-aging molecules, hydrates, firms and restructures your skin."  After using the duo for a week, I can attest that it does a half decent job moisturizing my face.  I have not noticed any firming, or restructuring however, nor age defying results.  I have to call it a failure in its primary mission, given that no one would consider paying this price if it were advertised solely as a moisturizer.  I will continue to use it because it claims to be a three week treatment, and will update if I notice anything new.  Otherwise, when this product is gone, I will return to using my more economical current favorite "anti-aging" moisturizer.

column6: Vitamin C serum 22 by serumtologie Anti Aging - 1.15 oz
column14:
First of all, the customer service from Serumtologie is AMAZING! Shortly after purchasing the product I received an email from Vanessa, the co-founder of the company and then several weeks after beginning usage I received a second "check-in" email to see how I liked the product and provide tips for not only using the product but maximizing my skin care routine! I have purchased a LOT through Amazon over the years and this is THE FIRST TIME a company has actually contacted me personally to ensure I was happy with their product.

Now on to the most important part, I LOVE THIS PRODUCT. I began using Serum 22 the morning after it arrived and have used it every day since without fail (about 3 weeks at this posting). I absolutely love the feel of this product on my skin. I have oily skin, aging skin AND I live in Florida which has tremendously high humidity so my skin, regardless of how well I try to take care of it, suffers from a fairly constant presence of some type of imperfection - usually nothing major - small bumps or breakouts - but rarely flawless. After incorporating this product into my routine for several weeks, I now look in the mirror and see radiant (not oily) skin! My pores are significantly less noticeable and my skin is well on its way to actually being flawless for the first time since I can remember. I noticed that I don't need as much cover-up and on many days I can actually get away with a light dusting of powder and be on my way! Honestly, were in not for the fact that my skin gets so oily in this humidity, I probably could actually go WITHOUT make-up for the first time in FOREVER.

This product is well on it's way to becoming a holy grail product for me and, for me, the customer service only seals the deal! Bravo Serumtologie!

column13: My aluminum free deodorant search is over!
column14: I have tried numerous aluminum free deodorants over the past couple of months to find the best one for me. This was really works the best. I've tried Trader Joe's (the worst), a roll on mineral, Tom's, and Schmidt's (burns and gave me bumps). The Lavanila doesn't burn, I don't get bumps, the scents are great (I've tried coconut/vanilla and vanilla), the application is smooth and not messy. It wipes on like a regular stick deodorant. It is very white when you first put it on. So you need to rub your armpits together until the white goes away if you plan on wearing a sleeveless shirt. Once the white is rubbed around, I have found that I can even wear a black sleeveless without it marking. My search is over and I am sticking with this one. It is very expensive I think though, with aluminum deodorants only being a few bucks, but worth it to not put aluminum into your system. Hence the 4 stars on the high price. I'd like to see a men's version with a manly smell, for the guys.

column6: Basil (linalool CT) Essential Oil 100% Pure, Undiluted, Therapeutic Grade.
column14:
Another great oil from Plant Therapy Essential Oils. Before I start the review of this five-star product, I wanted to mention a common problem: Once you start diffusing, you can't stop! If you are reading this, then you probably know what I am talking about. I am a beginner, and Plant Therapy's line of moderately priced Essential Oils has been a great introduction to diffusing that has allowed me to experiment with High-Quality 100% natural products. Their Basil (Linalool CT) is no different.

Basil essential oil has limitless uses. And while the many benefits have been discussed at length in other review, I purchased Basil specifically to use in a diffuser during the winter months, as Organic Facts indicates...
"Illness: Basil essential oil is effective in providing relief from colds, influenza and associated fevers. Due to its antispasmodic nature, it is frequently used to treat symptoms of whooping cough.
Respiratory: Along with its function in relieving coughs, it can also be used to treat asthma, bronchitis, and sinus infections."

Although this oil smells somewhat like the culinary basil scent that we are all familiar with, the scent is more complex. At the heart there is the basil(part of the mint family) essence. Additionally, there are subtle notes that some may perceive as citrus, woodsy, mint. All of these combine for a rare and complex oil for diffusing and another fiver-star product from Plant Therapy Essential Oils. [Note: It won't make you home smell like an Italian Restaurant!] Having tested several products in this category,
I received this item at a discounted price in exchange for my honest and unbiased review.

Relatively good razor for the money. Good shave, good charge.

I called up customer service, as the razor is under warranty. However, they won't send me a new razor without sending the old one in. Given that this is a product I use daily, and is not a cheap razor that has had major issues within a year, this is not ideal. I asked if they could put a hold on my credit card and send me a new razor preemptively, and then remove the charge when they got the broken one, and they said they could not.

In summary - poor display failed under a year, and customer service won't make my life easier. Not what I expect for a $200 product.

column13: Fights frizz. Refreshes styling products. Gives skin a healthy glow.
column14:
I am completely obsessed with this product! It has worked wonders for both my skin and my hair. I am plagued with a dry, itchy scalp. My hair is naturally wavy and tends to frizz no matter what. This product, however, is wonderful. After washing my hair, I spray it close to my scalp and then all over, using my fingers to spread the product through my hair. After blow drying, my hair feels sleek and smooth, yet not greasy like I've experienced with other products. It also helps to provide moisture to my scalp and keep the itching at bay.

I also love using this product to reactivate my styling aids. In the middle of a humid day, my hair will often start to frizz. I can spritz this product throughout my hair and smooth everything back out. It doesn't add weight to my hair or give a sticky feel. It just dries beautifully and makes my hair look just-styled.

In addition to using this product for my hair, I've also been using it as a facial mist. It's refreshing! I spray it on my face after washing, after applying makeup, or even when my makeup just needs a little freshen up in the middle of the day. It give a youthful, dewy glow. Because it's a light mist, there is also no issue with it causing my makeup to cake.

This product provides a wide variety of nutrients that are essential to both skin and hair, including Biotin. It is also free of harsh chemicals. I would recommend this product to anyone looking for a convenient, multi-purpose solution to dry skin, dry hair, and frizz.

This product was provided at a discount by the seller in exchange for my honest review.

column6: NIVEA Men Sensitive Face Wash
column14:
I was a huge fan of the Nivea Sensitive Face Wash that got discontinued a couple years ago and I actually bought a couple dozen bottles after it was discontinued because it was so great. When I saw this one in the store recently I was super excited - "they brought it back!" I thought. Unfortunately this is a completely different product than their old one and basically does the exact opposite of what they claim.

The first thing you'll notice is that it is LOADED with perfumes. Just opening the bottle you'll get a sense. It's basically stronger smelling than all the other face washes I've bought in the past couple years looking for a replacement of the originally Sensitive Face Wash. The smell is cheap and bad - I'd compare it to the fragrance of an Old Spice body wash. The first time I used it besides being annoyed by the smell, I felt it actually DID dry my skin out. Certainly more than the old formula but also probably more than any face wash I've used.

I tried it again and that night I basically sneezed all night. I thought perhaps sneezing all night was related to using it but figured it just was a coincidence. About a week later I tried it one last time and this time I sneezed all night again and basically got no sleep. This isn't something that happens to me a lot - the last time I stayed up all night sneezing was probably a year ago when I stayed in a house with lots of cats. So i feel about 99% sure that the heavy perfumes are causing an allergic reaction for me. Obviously everyone is different but I think one of the things many people are sensitive to is perfumes so it makes no sense that this product has so many.

There is a section on the back of the bottle titled "what you get" and this version and the old one are basically the same except the old has an additional bullet point saying "formula is soap, fragrance, dye and alcohol free to minimize the risk of skin irritation." The new bottle does notmake that claim because they clearly have lots of soap, fragrance, dye and alcohol.

It's just very frustrating that they discontinued a product that was so helpful and came up with a new one that is the exact opposite with the same branding as before. Why not sure keep a formula that is actually helpful for people with sensitive skin?

column14: Allow me to add to the comments about the branding.  "Pit Paste", really?  If you want to extend your appeal beyond places like Santa Cruz and Berkeley, you need to come up with a better name for the product and better packaging too.  Regarding the product, itself, I do like it.  I bought the unscented version and it actually has a modest but pleasant scent.  But the deodorant is so firm, that the Pit Paste folks suggest you hold the product under your arm for a few seconds to warm it up and allow it to soften.  Otherwise, it's like rubbing a large pencil eraser under your arm - feels pretty unfordable and not much product actually gets applied.  I find that it takes about 10 seconds for the product to warm up.  But once you do that, the product does apply and it works well.  It prevents body odor and seems to have no adverse effects.  The product would receive 5 stars if they could improve the formula to be softer and easier to apply and if they improved the "cringe" branding.

column14:
I can't give this a 1 star rating as I never got a chance to see if it works as intended. So I will be giving it 2 stars because I could not ever get the strips to stay properly applied for more than half an hour without popping up. At first I tried applying a strip long enough for the entire nail, but when trying to get the second side applied, the 1st side would pop up. It would seem my nail was too curved (though I wouldn't call it a big curve by any means) the instructions have an answer for this, and it's to start smaller and cut the strip small and cover the middle of the nail so it's not as bent. I tried that and it worked. I put on socks and went about my day. But about 30 minutes later, I took my sock off to inspect and it had popped up on one side. I took it off (it came off easily, even though the instructions say not to pull on it with force to remove), and tried again with another short strip. Same thing. 30 minutes pass and I feel it come undone

The only good thing I can say is that during the short periods it was applied, I felt discomfort, but that to me just meant it was most likely doing it's job. I really wanted these to work, but now I'll have to resort to old fashioned methods. At $50 dollars and only coming with 10 strips, this would be a great deal if they went on and stayed on as easily as implied by the site. But when you're throwing away strip after strip because the bonding process is very difficult, it becomes worrisome and seems like less of a deal

column6: Daily Rehydrating Sunscreen: SPF 30+ - Contains Vitamins B, C, E & Seaweed Extract - Rehydrating Skin Protection - Paraben & Fragrance Free - Broad Spectrum UVA / UVB Protection
column14:
I enjoy using this sunscreen, it feels great on my skin. It absorbs quickly and doesn't feel greasy or make me perspire while wearing it, which is important since I make sure I apply it before leaving the house. I am fair skinned so this SPC 30 works perfect for me. After years of sun exposure, I have seen the damage the sun can do to unprotected skin. Biopsies and having your skin frozen is not fun, best to make sure sunscreen is part of your normal routine!

This sunscreen (to me at least) does seem to have a slight fragrance, what I can smell is not unpleasant and is very faint. I apply this to exposed skin 30 minutes before leaving the house. This sunscreen is light enough to wear under makeup. I have even mixed a drop of my makeup into a few drops of sunscreen as a tint and then applied to my face. The A,B,C, and E vitamins, as well as the seaweed extract, does seem to lock in moisture and help my skin look nice and stay hydrated. Just make sure you reapply after a couple of hours, or if you swim or perspire.

Once I apply to my skin I can feel the difference, my skin feels really soft. It doesn't feels heavy or smell like coconuts and the beach, which makes it nice for daily use. For the past couple of days we've had 100+ degree weather here in Southern Calif., and this sunscreen has helped me keep from burning. I burn very easily, normally I would have started to pink up in about 10 minutes in this heat. I was running in and out of the house most of the day and got some color, but did not burn! :)

Free product sample received for review purposes.

*Updated 9/25/15 - We decided we were going to spend our anniversary on a whale watching cruise. It's been so hot here over the past few weeks and it was so much cooler on the coast. Mr. Doom & Gloom (my husband), looks at me as we're waiting to board the boat and says, " Ooooo you didn't bring a hat,...and you're wearing short sleeves too,...you're going to get so burnt! You'll be sorry tonight." :/
I had applied this sunscreen to all exposed skin 30 minutes before we left the house and tossed the bottle in my purse in case I needed to reapply later. I never did have to reapply, and after spending 3 hours on a boat and 30+ minutes waiting in line without shade I can honestly say this is the BEST sunscreen I've ever used!! I was a tiny bit pink later that evening but not burnt at all. column13: Great tool for uniform twists all over the head
column14:
This sponge is a great timesaver for making twists and dreads in curly african american hair.

To use this product, apply conditioner all over hair. Wait a few minutes and then rub the sponge (hole side down) in a circular motion all over the head. Make sure to rub in the same direction. What used to take hours for me to do by hand took about 15 minutes with this sponge.

The sponge will make tight, uniform curls all over the head. The longer you run, the more defined and closer to the scalp they are.

This sponge is particularly handy as you can use it on yourself.

I received this sponge for free in exchange for an honest review.

column14:
MaggardRazors sells a sampler pack of ToOBS scents which I'm quite happy I purchased. I most likely would have never tried this scent out, which would have been a terrible thing for me given how much I enjoy it. It's a pleasant, spicy scent that, in my eyes (and nose) practically screams "gentleman." The list of scents are on Fragrantica if anyone is interested in the reviews on it there.

As far as the shave itself, ToOBS is popular for a reason. I've used everything from hard soaps to soft creams and this is one of my favorites yet. Something worth noting - this is a thirsty cream. column13: Battery operated toothbrushes work great!! and the Toothpaste lightened my teeth!  I wish the toothbrush had a timer
column14:
I haven't owned an electric toothbrush in years so I don't know how they compare with battery operated toothbrushes; however, battery operated toothbrushes get my teeth much cleaner than manually brushing them. I've been using a battery operated toothbrush for about a year now.

The Spinbrush Radiant toothbrush gets my teeth just as clean as the Phillips Powerup.
I wish the Spinbrush would automatically turn off after 2 minutes. I deducted 1/2 star because it doesn't have a timer.

The Spinbrush toothbrush is not as jarring as Phillips Powerup battery operated toothbrush. However, the brush heads are thicker than the Powerup's; they're thicker than a regular toothbrush too. The thicker brush head is hard for me to get used to. Deducted 1/2 star for thick brush head.
UPDATE: I got used to the thicker brush head.

I used Arm & Hammer Brilliant Sparkle toothpaste for several years. It was a family favorite. When I couldn't find Brilliant Sparkle anymore, I purchased Advance White Extreme Whitening (I liked their Brilliant Sparkle formula better). This is the first time I've tried Truly Radiant and will update my review if I have a more radiant smile in 5 days.
Truly Radiant also strengthens your tooth enamel.

UPDATE: The toothpaste is great. My teeth are two or three shades whiter. It's hard to tell exactly without using a chart.

This kit has everything you need:
2 battery operated toothbrushes
1 tube of Arm & Hammer Truly Radiant toothpaste
2 replacement brushes
4 pre-installed AA batteries (2 for each toothbrush)

When I mentioned that I was using a battery operated toothbrush to my dental hygenist, she asked how much the replacement heads were. Apparently many people don't buy electric toothbrushes because the electric toothbrush & replacement heads cost quite a bit.
If that's a concern of yours, give this battery operated toothbrush a try. It's more affordable.

When I gave my grandkids (ages 4 & 5) a child's battery operated toothbrush, they were really excited & told their parents how much cleaner their teeth felt.

One star deducted because the toothbrush doesn't have a timer & the brush head is thicker than the average brush head.

column6: Neutrogena Facial Treatment, All-in-1 Acne Control, 1 fz (Pack of 3)
column13: Neutrogena All-in-one Acne Treatment and its WORTHLESS \replacement\""
column14:
Neutrogena, you have made a poor business decision in discontinuing the All-in-one Acne Facial Treatment, a poor business decision that I hope you will reconsider. I am 27 years old and have been suffering from mild to severe hormonal acne since I was 16. I have been using the All-in-one Acne Facial Treatment for about 3 years. It has made all the difference in the world in my appearance, the feel and health of my skin, and my confidence level. I tried many other products, discovering that I am allergic to benzoyl peroxide and that most anti-acne regimes are terrible for my skin because their goal is to dry it out completely. Salicylic acid is the only known alpha hydroxy acid; it is lipid soluble and penetrates the follicle and breaks down excess sebum, allowing the follicle to drain. But because it does this, salicylic acid on it's own can be rather harsh and can leave the skin horribly dry and vulnerable to cracking and thus more susceptible to bacteria. This is especially true when it is applied to a sensitive skin like mine.
Luckily, I discovered the All-in-one Acne Facial Treatment, which I began to use in conjunction with the All-in-one Acne Facial Scrub and the Pink Grapefruit Scrub (I believed that adding a beta hydroxy acid to the use of the alpha hydroxy acid would be helpful, understanding that although it is only water soluble, it is proven to break down dead skin cells on the surface). The results were almost immediate and amazing. I experimented a bit and tried just the scrubs. That left my skin far too dry and peeling. The All-in-one Acne Facial Treatment moisturized my skin overall and left it feeling smooth, even, and silky, while it healed ruptured acne and soothed it, and made new acne disappear within two days at most. I was hoping that it would help my acne, but that it achieved this AND made my skin incredibly soft and smooth was a pleasant surprise! This is because it is a moisturizing cream formula. As I have done more research, I havediscovered another reason for this. In addition to being anti-aging and anti-wrinkle, retinol is used against acne because, just like salicylic acid, it speeds up skin cell regeneration by breaking down excess sebum and dead skin cells. I have tried the best products containing retinol and find that the All-in-one Acne Facial Treatment is far superior, even as an anti-aging product. I have concluded that salicylic acid is as good as if not superior to retinol in fighting wrinkles, despite the fact that it is not advertised as such.
The All-in-one Acne Facial Treatment has changed my life. I am an athlete and I work in high end retail. My appearance makes a difference to my level of success. I used to have to get up so much earlier to fit in my makeup routine because I had to cover up my acne thoroughly. Or I would forego my workout routine because I knew my skin would have to dry after showering to be ready for the makeup I had to use to cover my acne. And I often could not wear scoop necklines or V backs because I was far to embarrassed by my acne, especially where my sports bra chafed and irritated my skin. But the All-in-one Acne Facial Treatment (which I frankly wish you offered in much bigger tubes) changed all of that! I apply it right after my shower to my damp skin. It has improved my skin so much and has improved my daily routine. I work out, shower quickly, apply the treatment, throw clothes on without worrying about whether they cover up acne (because it isn't there!), apply a minimal amount of makeup, and feel like a boss all day. The All-in-one Acne Facial Treatment has done all of this.
It has been discontinued. As soon as I discovered this, I read as many reviews as possible, attempting to discover why you have discontinued this product. But almost all the reviews were favourable. Some were reminiscent of my own experience. I called your customer service number. The representative was polite, but clearly had no intention of relaying my clear messages to her higher ups. She recommended a different product. I was skeptical because I had tried a Clearasil gel formula before and it was awful.

I decided to give the Rapid Clear 2-in1 Fight and Fade Gel a chance. But because it is a gel and not a soothing cream, it irritates the surface of the skin, leaving it dry, red, and cracking. It does nothing to heal ruptured acne. Moreover, a gel formula makes it so that the substance sticks to itself. It is NOT absorbed by the skin! It forms a layer that sits on the skin's surface and when the skin is moved too much (i.e. smiling, talking, raising an eyebrow, laughing, breathing), this layer breaks apart and peels off, turning into a disgusting coagulated mess. It also did this as soon as I tried to add a sunscreen or makeup. I then attempted to only use it at night, only to find that it peeled off and little bits of it were all over my pillow. In short, this product is awful. I am infinitely disappointed that you have replaced such a reliable, effective product as the All-in-one Acne Facial Treatment with this inferior product that Clearasil and Clean and Clear already have out on the market. And I am resentful that your Customer service representative recommended it to me.
I understand if your plan is to reintroduce the treatment cream in an improved formula (with 2% salicylic acid content rather than 1% and/or with glycolic acid added for example), however, why discontinue the former when you are not ready to release the new one?

column6: Perfecto Deluxe Shaving Kit, 100% Badger Shaving Brush, Chrome Razor and Brush Stand and Chrome Double Edge Safety Razor
column14: Would I buy it again? No.  First off the strongest item in this set is the stand. Its beautiful, its heavy, and has an all around quality to it.  As for the brush, I have read a few reviews that say you shouldnt really buy a badger brush unless its a bit more cash. Im gonna go out on a limb here and say I agree. This brush, while does indeed work, and is an authentic badger brush, isnt that great. I can already tell its not gonna last "years". Maybe it will, but the brush itself will probably be crummy and hairless by the end of one year. I realize its normal for the brush to shed a FEW hairs for the first month or two, but this thing is averaging 7 lost hairs per shave. Maybe I got a bum brush? Probably not, as I go into the razors review, but its far more of a pain in the rear to return this entire set....than to push forward.  Now the razor. You are probably buying this set because you are new to wet shaving (like myself). Be aware that the perfecto razor (which can also be purchased separately outside this kit, is a very "aggressive" shave. Do your homework because you can EASILY take a decent amount of skin off your face with an angle that is too sharp, or a crummy lather. I have a nice area of red scar tissue that is still healing two weeks later. While my technique is definitely improving daily, this razor leaves little room for error, and will let you know when your "skills" are lacking. Maybe thats a good thing? Baptism by fire ya know?  But my BIGGEST problem with this kit is that the razor itself lacks in construction. When you unscrew the handle from the head to change a razor, there is another the handle can unscrew from directly under the primary tightening location. If you are unlucky like me, the handle wont screw off from the head but the handle will unscrew off from itself (if that makes any sense). I was running late for work and needed to change a blade after I noticed the one I had tugging. I attempted to unscrew the handle and the head was locked shut as I unscrewed it from itself. It took me 10 min running around like a buffoon in my underwear trying to get the darn head open. I had to grab PLIERS! from the garage just to get this thing separated. I ended up super gluing the handle back to the small piece it unscrewed from and hopefully this fixes the problem.  Either way, I would splurge a few extra bucks. Buy the stand by itself, get a boar brush if you are trying to save cash, and splurge and extra $10 and get a razor of higher quality. I did the math and if I can get "6 months" out of this purchase, I will break even and can try with a new razor in my quest to save money and have a better shave.

But, this soap will go to my husband. *8-20-15 addendum to original review: I will say, as soon as I posted this review, at 3 stars, I received an email from the company. Quickest customer service ever. Offered immediately to see what they could do to make my experience better. I thought, wow. How great. I have never even been contacted by a company that I have given a one star for, let alone a three.  So, he explained, since the bars are produced by batch, this batch may have had more chocolate in it. Which, now that my nose and brain have a frame of reference, is what I smell. Chocolate, not coffee. He also sent more bars to see if we could find one that matched my scent palate better. One fit the bill for my hubby well, island drift, and one fit my sensitive nose, goats milk citrus twist. And as before, they are hydrating and don't leave a strong odor on your skin after, which we like. Thanks soap company, you restore my faith in customer service and buying from small companies.

That said, this is a quick, cost effective alternative to having your lashes tinted in a salon. I've paid for professional lash tinting before and my at-home results with this product are comparable. I have been using Latisse for about two months and while my lashes are noticeably longer, they are too blonde to show up without makeup. This product helps a lot. I used regular clean cotton swabs to apply the liquid, then applied the gel with a clean mascara spoolie instead of the comb that came with the kit. Personal preference. I started out with the shield papers under my eyes, but I ended up throwing them away and proceeding without them. If you dab a little eye cream on the skin around your eyes before starting and keep a clean damp cotton swab handy for wiping off goofs, you shouldn't have to worry too much about rogue stains. I did get a little bit of the gel in one eye and it stung like a beast for maybe fifteen seconds, but I blinked it out easily and the redness went away about a minute after the stinging stopped. It didn't prevent me from finishing the job or affect my results, so I still think this deserves five stars. I am particularly delighted with the short processing time. I did one eye at a time, first the bottom lashes, then the top, so I repeated the whole process four times. I was still done in less than fifteen minutes. Can't beat that.

column13: Great razor at a great price!
column14: My shaving setup is Trumpers Rose shave cream and a Vulfix Super Badger Brush. Blades used: Astra Super Stainless (came with the razor) 3 stars Personna Blue 3 stars Rapira Platinum Lux 4 stars Feather Stainless 5 stars  This is a great razor for the beginning wet shaver or the experienced one. This is a very mild razor. I would directly compare this to an Edwin Jagger DL89. Shave wise I see no difference. The razor is well crafted. There is no play in the razor head. I have been shaving with this razor for 2 weeks with a variety of blades. I did knock off 1 star for an issue with the paint. There was a small piece of dirt that had gotten under the paint. This was on the top plate on the bottom side at the edge where it would come in contact with the blade the most. This in turn caused the blade to warp. A quick session with a pocket knife and the issue was fixed. I have not had the paint chip like other reviewers. The paint actually gave a more positive grip on the razor. All in all this is a great addition to my razor collection, This will be in my regular rotation.

column14:
Finally - something that works without aluminum & white residue (when applied per the instructions)!

Being a "very blessed" woman (shout-out to you, S Mares) living in 100+ deg F heat in the summer, I have struggled with below & between breast moisture issues for most of my adult life. The options I've tried for keeping moisture at bay on a longer basis include aluminum-containing products or baby powder/corn starch powders that left serious white patches on the skin & clothing.

I am so pleased with this product. It hasn't completely wiped out all of the moisture (Hello, 100+ deg F heat), but it has mostly kept it at bay. You have to follow the instructions - shake well before use (or it may be watery) and spread evenly & thinly to avoid white patches / streaks on the skin. You also need to let it completely dry & wash your hands before putting on clothing or you'll get white marks on your clothes.

This was a great find & I will definitely be reordering on a regular basis.

I've owned convertible sports cars for most of my adult life, and my wife is always had trouble writing in one because the wind messing up her hair. A few years back I suggested she start using one of the long clips for holding her hair. Problem was that it just didn't seem to hold as well when in a car at 65 miles an hour or more. So when I saw all these Sectioning Alligator Clips, with the large teeth, I thought it was worth getting to see if it works any better. After all, the price was good and overall it look like a product well worth a try.

I'm glad to report that my first evaluation approved to be very accurate. Not only do the clips hold her hair well while in the ragtop but they've also become a favorite of hers for a number of jobs in the garden around the house. She is even taken to wearing the clips as a fashion accessory and find them exceptionally well designed for holding longer hair. I can imagine a better review for product like this and I guess in the long run I'm saying that I would recommend this product to anyone else who wants to hold their hair securely.

column6: Natural Way Organics Organic Mens Lotion for Hands & Body - 8 oz [Misc.] [Misc.]
column13: Good lotion but pungent and therefore unusable
column14: Upon opening this product which arrived today,I was dismayed first to observe that some of the lotion had started leaking from the bottle.  I will be contacting Amazon about this. Alone, this is a resolvable problem and not worthy of a poor review. What really matters is the product itself. From a skin softening standpoint, the lotion does work and it isn't terribly greasy. But what makes it unusable by me at least, is the extremely strong scent. This is not a masculine scent at all -- it is a cross between a moth-repelling cedar hanger and an artificial rose/floral scent (think cheap women's perfume). I am not sensitive to smell and indeed, with my current allergies, my sense of smell is diminished. The aroma of this lotion cuts through my stuffed up nose,  and having only applied it to my hands, I can smell it on me as I type this review. I certainly will not be buying this again and I do not recommend it. Why is it hard to make a natural lotion with recognizable ingredients and a subtle scent? It certainly is possible -- subtract the natural fragrances and non-moisturizing, non-nutritive essential oils from this product and I'm sure it would be fine. I am not sure how anyone could classify this as a "light" scent and I certainly won't be ordering it again.

column6: Renpure Solutions Cleansing Conditioner, Rosemary Mint, 16 Fluid Ounce
column13: Awesome stuff, awesome price, meh scent.
column14:
I see a lot of negative reviews of this stuff on here and I think it's mostly because of the foreign concept of a cleansing conditioner. It's not going to foam up like a conventional shampoo because A, there's no SLS in it and B, it's more of the consistency of a conditioner. So just pretend like you're just going to use conditioner on your hair and you'll be fine.

That being said, there are some tricks to getting the most out of this stuff. First, use waaaay more than the directions say to use, especially if you've got crazy long/thick/curly hair like I do. I work it through in sections, paying really good attention to the crown of my head because thats where I had trouble the first 1-2 times I used this. Massage the crap out of your scalp, and then comb the stuff all the way down to your ends. If you've got fuzzy ends like I tend to get, put some more on the ends. Leave it on for a few minutes, but seriously not a lifetime. Then rinse! It's really not rocket science.

I'm not wild about the scent of this one, but it doesn't last too long like other shampoos so I didn't remove any stars for that. I'll just try a different scent next time. All in all, I'm a cleansing conditioner convert thanks to this stuff (ps - I've never tried Wen or any of the other products like it, so maybe I'm missing out, but this stuff satisfies my needs for $10 instead of $32 haha). Oh! And this bottle lasted me about 2 months washing twice a week, so if you're a daily hair washer, maybe this isn't the best thing out there for you.

column13: most leakproof bottle I've ever seen.  Impressed!
column14:
I was pleasantly surprised by these travel bottles. I already have little plastic bottles for my gym/pool bag. How much better could these be? Let me tell you: these things are great. Because they're soft silicone, I can squeeze every last drop out! No more banging the bottle or shaking it trying to get some out when it's low. No seams to fight against when I squeeze hard to dispense an almost empty bottle.

Lid is plastic. It removes easily for easy filling. But once lid is back on and top is closed, the bottle stays closed. If I squeeze a closed one, I can't get it to leak.

I tried manhandling them a bit to probe for weaknesses, but they are durable.

PROS
Extremely easy to get product out of
Easy to fill.
Excellent seal: doesn't leak even under pressure!
3 ounce size is TSA approved for airline use
Comes in easy-to-open packaging

CONS
Would love to see this company also offer a larger size for gym/pool/roadtrip use. I understand 3oz is the limit for air travel, but these things are great for so many other places!

column6: Ava Anderson Non-Toxic Sunscreen 30+ SPF, 2.9 oz
column13: Works! Buy direct and follow instructions!
column14: It works!! If you buy it direct and follow the instructions. I'm not sure why anyone would pay 3-5 times as much to order this on Amazon, but you have no idea what you are getting, if the product has been damaged, etc. It is super sketchy. That said, I bought direct from Ava Anderson Non-Toxic. Tested on myself first at the beach before testing on my kids. It works! And doesn't make my children's exzema flare. It's been a godsend for us. This is natural, zinc based sunscreen with organic oils. This means you need to apply at least 15 minutes before going out. Most importantly, you must knead the tube each time you apply AND knead in your hand to be sure nothing has settled and you are getting an even amount of zinc, which acts as a physical barrier to sun's rays vs most (harmful) chemical sunscreens. You also need to reapply after swimming/sweating, etc. Remember this isn't being absorbed into your skin like chemical sunscreens-which is a good thing!! But it does mean you need to reapply and follow the directions carefully. It's been SO worth the little bit of extra effort for my family. Before this I was using Water Babies on my kids, not knowing it was one of the top rated "worst" and "most harmful" for kids as rated by Environmental Working Group and other objective researchers.
