column6: DRAPER/HOLM - Soulful Organic Patchouli and Cedarwood Perfume (.3 FL OZ Roll-on Bottle)
column14:
Love this blend! Very well balanced, the scent is a mix of earthy tons, wood but not too heavy. It's a great perfume or blend to use for calming. Have used it actaully during meditation and it's meant to help soothe and calm out your nerves, my son likes this rolled onto his pillow at night. It's taken over the lavender he used to fall asleep with.
Very grounding, very balanced. I create many of my own blends but this has got to be one of the most relaxing ones I've come across that is pre-blended.While it is an earthy wood scent don't let it steer you away ladies, it's been a fantasy perfume so far and I've had many compliments. Wish I could have this in a dropper bottle and use in a diffuser actaully, but really enjoy the roller ball. Best areas to place, is wrists, neck , even above your heart. Roller balls are handy to take traveling, they are small for pockets, take up so little room you don't notice. I will say that if you press too hard you will end up having too much oil on your skin, would just recommend gently rolling there's no need to be firm with it. The blend is patchouli, cederwood and based with jojoba oil ( carrier) unisex the scent is really perfect for anyone. I have noticed in the heat it carries really thick, ( not bad, but you will notice it more) so be mindful of that, a little does go a long way but other than that I really enjoy this balanced blend . Comes in a cute tin container, which I love, so you can reuse that after you've finished the roller ball, a little tip- once you are done with the roller ball, pop that plastic roller out and place some Epson salt inside ( bath salts) . The salt will absorb the oil along the glass and you can add that into a bath, so very relaxing! Would recommend this to any of my friends, makes a great gift!

This light weigh easy to use dryer has triple ceramic coating that provides heat distribution which penetrates hair quickly and that cuts drying time. The tourmaline ionic technology eliminates static electricity and frizz. There are three heat settings cool, warm and hot. A new feature to me is the cool shot which I find helpful for post shower hot flashes.

The handle has a textured hand grip that helps with wet hands. Also there is a round blowout brush, a concentrator attachment and two sectional clips that aid in styling your hair. My styling/blowout time has decreased and that allows me another cup of coffee before leaving for work. This makes me a happy lady.”

column6: Braun Silk-épil 7 Wet and Dry Epilator, White
column14:
I recently received this epilator to review, by BzzAgent.
I've always wanted to try an epilator, but was always afraid to. Now that this little miracle tool has come into my life, I may never shave my legs again! Started with my underarms, just to get one of the most sensitive parts over with first (brave, I know!). That was scary at first, but I quickly realized that the anticipation was worst than the actual pain. Although it missed a few strays here and there, they were very easy to spot thanks to the bright beam of light. I went over them and they were quickly eliminated. Then, I decided to do my lower and upper legs. Lower legs were a snap and did not hurt at all. Upper legs were fine too, just a tiny discomforting on the inner upper thighs. Now, the bikini area... That was a whole other ball game. Front was easy, but definitely not painless, as I have very course hair there. After much flinching and toe curling, I was able to get thru most of it. On the sides, it pinched my skin once and left tiny red marks and that was really painful, but also my fault, as I did not stretch the skin enough. I decided to leave well enough alone and not get too close... I'll leave the more delicate areas to my trusty old razor, for now. All in all, I will continue to use this epilator mainly because it's quick, easy and for the most part tolerable. I can't wait to see how long the results last. I'm a true believer!

column6: BohoTats Flash Tattoos - Set of 5 Sheets - Over 100+ Intricate Designs - Stunning Metallic Flashtats - Non Toxic - Quality Guarantee - Temporary Metallic Tattoos
column14:
I have been seeing these tattoos everywhere and they look so different than the normal temporary ones I usually wear. I finally broke down and ordered a set. They look so neat and beautiful right out of the package. I could not wait to put one or a few on. My daughter immediately wanted to put one on as well. She is four but loves anything girly or glittery. We both had a fun picking out what we wanted and was excited to put them on.

This set comes with five sheets of metallic tattoos. Each sheet has several different designs on it. I am a sucker for feathers. These stand out and pop on your skin even if you have fair skin such as I. I am in love with the color combos used.

To apply the tattoos:
You cut around the desired tattoo, close as you can get.
Remove the plastic.
Place the tattoo side down onto the skin.
Press the tattoo backing with a wet wash cloth.
Slowly peel the backing paper off.

These last a long time on the skin, but it always depends on where you put it. I did put some on my fingers and they stayed on really well without fading even after washing my hands a lot. We went swimming for a bit and the tattoo was still intact-ed afterwards. The tattoos were so easy to apply that my four year old did one all on her own. These are fun and go with just about any outfit you are planning on wearing. You can wear a few without it being too much. One thing I love the most is I can't wear any type of jewelry right now as my son pulls on it. These are the next best thing. You can feel pretty and look awesome in these without having your kids pulling on them.

I received this product at a deep discount for my honest and unbiased opinion.

column6: Carol's Daughter Ecstasy Dry Oil Mist for Unisex, 4 Ounce
column13: Amazing scent and staying power, no icky chemicals
column14:
I've been obsessed with this scent since I first smelled it in a body wash several years ago. The natural next step, of course, would be to order it in a fragrance, but I was worried that since this is technically an oil for moisturizing and not an EDT or EDP there would be barely any staying power. Well, quite the opposite, to my pleasant surprise! The scene still fades by the end of the day, but there is at least a trace of it, whereas just about all actual perfumes I wear completely vanish within a few hours. I think I just have a skin-type or body temperature that eats up fragrance, unfortunately.

The other amazing thing about this is the ingredients area almost all just natural fragrance oils and things that moisturize your skin while scenting it, not scary-sounding chemicals and alcohols like in true perfumes. Not to mention, it really does make your skin glow because of the oils.

As for the scent itself, it's very sweet and feminine, without being little-girlish or candy-like. Normally I loathe musks (one of the three notes of this is Egyptian musk), but maybe that's what makes it not sickeningly sweet.

If you've ever smelled Bodycology's Moroccan Sunset (you can find it at Target or drug stores, I believe), it's similar to that, but maybe a little more sophisticated. That's another thing - the notes are strawberry, mango and Egyptian musk, but blended together, I don't feel like I smell like any one of those things. They are combined in such a way that you just smell sweet and feminine but also sexy and exotic. Love!

column6: Cellulite Defense Gel-Cream - Cellulite Cream w Caffeine + Retinol + Seaweed; Firming & Toning Gel - Use Solo or as the Perfect Companion w Massager, Brush, Scrub, Roller or other Remover Treatment…
column13: I loved everything about this cream
column14: When I first ordered this product, six or seven weeks ago, I received the jar with the red label and white print. I loved everything about this cream, most especially that it dramatically softened my skin right away. So much so, that I would have considered using it in non-cellulite areas as a regular moisturizer. When I finished my first jar, knowing both customers and company indicated it may be weeks before I'd see a difference in the actual cellulite, I put in a new order for two jars. I then received two different jars (with the new silver band on the front). This formula seems very different to me. For one, the color is a disturbing beige (the previous one was white; was this intended to give customers a visible sense of the caffeine content? LOL). The new cream also seemed to have higher concentrations of whatever menthol-type agent was used, and it did not leave my skin's texture as soft as the previous cream. This new cream's impact on the cellulite is also different. Rather than changing the cellulite slowly but steadily over time, this new cream changes it more visibly faster but the change also seems to be more temporary. I've decided to finish out my two jars before considering another option.

column6: Roller-540 Needles 0.25mm Needle Tool Pack with Cute Ball Pen
column13: Derma Rollers are Great: This Particular One Sucks
column14: Having used derma rollers in the past, I know what is needed in terms of quality and expectations. And no, I do not believe that you need an expensive roller in order to get the "best" results.  The big issue with this particular derma roller is that the needles on this roller are not consistent in size (i.e. one side of the roller's needles are longer than the other).  Additionally, the needles, upon rotating the roller, are uneven and inconsistent in length. These two add up to big problems in terms of rolling and seeing results, since you will not know which areas have been properly treated or not. Perhaps I had a dud, but I am not willing to take the risk in reordering this style again.  Do yourself a favor and find another brand to go with. I've had success with the MT brand [[ASIN:B00U20HRBS Facial Skin Care Needle Titanium Micro Acne Scars Derma Skin Roller Stretch Mark 0.5mm]], but there are others out there.

column14: For those of you who have seen the Breakfast Club, I was that weird girl in detention who could make it snow dandruff by simply rubbing my scalp. I had so many problems with scabbing, itching and flaking I thought the only logical explanation could be psoriasis. I tried all sorts of natural remedies such as the vinegar, baking soda and water solution to coconut and tea tree oils and all kinds of 'miracle shamoos' that simply did not work 100%. Maple Holistics has been god sent. The winter duo is my absolute favorite. Yes, you will smell like spearmint fresh out of the shower but once it dries, it quickly subsides so do not be concerned about that. I can get away with washing once every 3 days easily, well my hair that is anyways. I also highly recommend the dead sea mud mask and the silk 18 conditioner works just as well and has a lovely vanilla scent. I can now successfully mock the herbal essence commercials with execution thanks to Maple Holistics. Oh and did I mention the cost for this magic in a bottle can be all yours for about just $12. column14:

I had seen the smaller version of this one on Amazon and finally came across the big one. It measures 4" as described. I really like claws like this that have flat teeth, so that they rest against your head instead of sticking out even more. The teeth are spaced fairly close and quite grippy.

The only con is that the opening at both ends is narrower than I thought due to the design. The space right above teeth is very small and my thick hair takes up a lot of space. After placing the claw around my twist of hair, I have to squeeze the claw a bit more to make the twist narrower, so that more hair goes toward the tabs section of the clip. column13: I found it's extremely easy to put on
column14: This is my first wig and I wasn't sure how it was going to look on me or if I would even be able to put it on correctly. I found it's extremely easy to put on, the wig cap goes on your head first and you pull it down so it's around your neck, make sure the thick part is on the bottom, then pull the other side back over your head keeping the thick part at your forehead line, pulling all of the rest of your hair into the rest of the cap, And then you put the wig on.  The bangs are long but that's good because everyone's head is shaped differently so if you have a longer face the bangs might be just right for you where as for me they're pretty long and I may want to trim them a little bit. I love the length and color. It also comes with a little wig comb so you can comb it and keep it looking nice. It is a great wig for cosplay, Halloween, drag, role playing at home if you know what I mean, or just to go out with a change of hair. It's a very good quality wig and the wig cap not the wig makes my head itch. I would definitely recommend this to someone looking for a long purple Schlake the waves in the hair are fabulous and I love the way it looks on me. These are absolutely my very own honest opinions after having received and tried this product for free in exchange for an unbiased and honest review.

column6: Clairol Shimmer Lights Shampoo + Conditioner (Combo Deal)…
column13: The best, I have dyed middle golden blonde hair
column14:
The best , I have dyed middle golden blonde hair , after shampoo 2 min and conditioner for 5 min my hair become light ash blonde , I tried other products without success , the hair are nice after the conditioner , so if you use your own shampoo the conditioner will be enough as the pigment is more strong than in the shampoo my nail polish was gray from white so wear gloves .. the skin was ok .
The shampoo did nothing to my hair as there was not change in color at all .
Don't use the product straight after bleaching to a pale yellow or white as you hair can turn purple-bluish , the hair after bleach are very absorbing , mix half- half with your regular conditioner unless you hair turn golden blonde or have orange tone you can go for max power as well as it will tone them nice down to middle ash blond .
This product is so much better than dye hair toner that damage bleached hair even more , my hair are long to my lower back bleached to dead, but soft , shiny and looks healthy and don't break down .. nice product and recommended

I have only one negative comments about what is the smell , it remind me of cheap Brazilian perfume , my hands smell 2 days after wash and wash not to mention the hair , too intensive and my boyfriend don't like it , but hey, better smelly beautiful hair than bald head lol you can't have everything ! always paying for something back right ?

column14:
I have been using Dove products for many years and they are a trusted brand in our house. When it comes to deodorant, I am very picky. Let's face it, it's not something we want to have an epic fail with when we try a new product! I was hesitant. I normally use either the Dove Clinical Protection or the Degree Clinical Protection deodorant.

The Advance Care Original Clean Dove Deodorant goes on clean and smooth - fresh smelling, nothing overpowering here. That's what I want. I don't want a fragrance to mask a smell! I don't want a smell to begin with! I put the Advance Care to the test!

I have to admit, even on a summer day, it held its own. The only thing that I miss between this and the advance care is the application aspect. I miss the tiny holes that help break up the solid so that it goes on smoother. (See pics below for the comparison to show you what I mean) Other than that, this won for price point, getting the job done and overall value!

Thanks Dove, you added another winner to the team!

column14:
I bought this contour palette when it was in an Outlet catalog, and I can't say enough about how lovely the texture and colors are. The brown is a perfect soft matte contour color for pale to light/medium skintones, and just as it looks, is almost a delicate milk chocolate shade-- and makes a beautiful sheer eye color base as well. The peach tone is soft, yet has a gentle vibrancy-- I have extremely pale skin with neutral undertones, and have never been able to wear orange-y peach tones well-- this is not orange-y, not pink peach, but more of a true peach tone. I have been wearing the matte brown virtually ever day since I got it, as a contour, mostly, but also as color, eyeshadow, or a soft liner.

The highlighter shade has the merest bit of fine soft glimmer-- it's almost really a matte like the other two, and works on top of either/both the other colors, and anywhere you want to bring a contouring glow without shimmery effect. I use it everyday as a final redness-hiding touch on my lower lashline, especially in the inner corner.

Suitable for all skin types, even dry (as mine is 3/4 of the year) when properly prepped. Wears nicely.

column13: Pampering your face within your own home.
column14: This face masque has a unique smell that I cannot tell if I like it or not. I get like a cucumber like scent by then a straight up pill like smell. Like when you open Tylenol and you smell that powered smell being released. So in certain spots I get a sweet smell and than another I get a scent that I'm not fond of, at all. That doesn't effect the performance of the masque, just wanted to point that out. On the jar it states to put it on for 5 minutes or longer. I've been doing mine for about 8 minutes and that seems to be ideal for my skin. It has a lotion like consistency and a peach like color to it. Between the scent and the color, I wasn't expecting anything appealing to the eye or nose in the least. Though the smell is a hit or miss, it's not the worst smelling skincare product that I've used. I like that as soon as I remove it from my face I can instantly feel the difference from the before and after feel. My skin feels so much firmer and much more smooth to the touch. (My skin isn't rough feeling if I don't use this.) The smell does linger through the use of it and it seems to last around 30 minutes to an hour after I've taken it off, but it's more on a faint side once it's removed. When applying and taking it off I use a circular motion. I'm not sure if that makes a difference or not for the container just says to gently massage it onto the skin. The wet washcloth, to remove the masque, seems to be the best bet. No reason to make a huge mess as you continuously wet your hands and attempt to remove it from your face. I did receive this at a discounted rate for my unbiased review. My opinion was not influenced by the discount that I received.

column6: Anti Cellulite Coffee Kona Scrub with Dead Sea Salts - 24oz - All Natural - Coffee Scrubs Are Great Body Scrubs for Reducing Cellulite and Stretch Marks
column13: That's pretty great because you can leave it in the shower ...
column14:
First let me be clear, I did not pay full price for this, I got a discount in order to test and review the product. I am sure that makes you want to ignore everything I'm about to say, but please- don't.

First, the product comes in a resealable package. That's pretty great because you can leave it in the shower and not worry about it getting wet or ruined. (You do have to make sure the track stays clear of grainy product or it takes a second to seal shut.)

Now, on to the good stuff

This is by far the single greatest scrub I have EVER used, and I have used A LOT.

The smell is the most rich delicious smell I have encountered. Mine was coconut and I don't know how to describe the small of coffee and coconut (I don't even like coconut) but think of a morning on the beach with your fresh coffee covered in coconut oil. The grains consist of two types, the coffee grounds and the exfoliating ones. They are mixed with an oil based product which makes sliding the product over your body less painful than some products I have had in the past which sort of felt like sandpaper. When you rinse off your skin is so silky and shiny (the oil is like a really rich moisturizer that makes my skin have a natural shine and my legs look amazing...)

The only issue I had was the first time I took a bath I came back the next morning to what looked like a beach in my bathtub, so make sure you rinse out after you are done.

I would be happy to answer ANY questions you have, I have already gone through my first package (it lasted about 3.5 weeks of every day application and use on the heavy side because I was trying to test it, I would expect about a month or more) and have purchased my second at full price.

I can't account for all the scents, but after this next package I am going to experiment and will update my review.

column14: This device worked great. [[ASIN:B00AUTKHHM Emjoi Micro-Pedi Battery Operated Callus Remover]] I bought it in October 2014, but last month, July 2015,  the bottom cap that holds the batteries in came off and fell apart. Consequently the device wouldn't function until I taped it shut.  I submitted a request for a replacement to ShaveNow (the seller) and was just sent an automated "Expiration of returns period".  I paid $24.95 for this device and it lasted less than a year,  with pretty light use -  once or twice a month.  Since I had bought additional rollers I bought the updated version [[ASIN:B005XUNG5I Emjoi Micro-Pedi Nano Callus Remover]], so that those wouldn't be a complete waste too.  I hope this one lasts longer.  I find the Amazon review program very useful,  but wish there was an automated mechanism that asked buyers to review the product's durability in a reasonable timeframe.

column6: Brights Semi Permanent Hair Color
column14:
I bleached my hair over a week ago and then last night I used three tubes of this product on my hair. I had two people helping me to make sure everything was covered and then left it in for over 40 minutes. When I washed it out it looked more like a blue-purple than an actual purple, but to my horror I found that nearly 50% of my hair wasn't purple. It left the un-purple parts of my hair a gray-brown color. I've dyed my hair many times, but never used this brand before and never will again.

The day before I also used a natural dye by this brand on my boyfriend's sister and it also turned out horribly. I was supposed to be a natural blonde, but turned out orange. I should have returned all the purple I bought for myself after that!

Horrible product, but here's the rest of the review all the same: Didn't have a bad smell, more like grape scented markers. Came as a thick paste that goes straight into your hair, which is convenient and low-mess; however, it makes it more tedious to apply than the more liquid types of dyes. Like with most dyes, keep a damp paper towel with dish soap on it nearby to easily wipe dye off skin to prevent unwanted dying.

I purchased this product for my mother (49) to try and help firm and tighten her face and neck. She absolutely loves this product, she can tell a significant difference from before to now.
She has used this product for about two weeks, her wrinkles are less noticeable and she feels like her face, neck and her eyes are firmer. It pumps out just enough to use on her targeted areas. She loves that it does not have a heavy feel to it, and it goes on very easily. It also does not have an overly intense smell to it either, it is very mild compared to other products she has tried in the past. The only thing she dislikes about the product is that it is a little sticky feeling after applying to the face, but it becomes smooth and absorbs into the skin within 30 seconds to 1 minute.
From my point of view, I can see a difference in my mother's skin, ESPECIALLY her neck, which has been her biggest issue. Her skin looks and feels smoother, and the wrinkles are less noticeable.
My mother and I both highly recommend this product to anyone who is looking for plastic surgery results without the cost and surgery. This is a great price for amazing results.

I did receive this product at a reduced cost to provide my honest and unbiased opinion and this review is of my own without any compensation from the provider.

column6: The Magic Pads - 2% Glycolic Acid Pads with USDA Certified Organic Extracts, 60 Count
column14:
Like almost ever acne sufferer I've tried everything. Every supplement, wash, herb, essential oil, cream... Antibiotics, retin-a, proactiv, the list goes on and on.

This, like most everything, didn't do anything. I've had moderate to sever acne for over 10 years now and only three things have helped me personally:
1) Burdock root. For about a year, then I feel like my body may have gotten used to it or something.. I still take it on and off just for fun.
2) Papaya soap. For some crazy reason, I dunno.
3) and most importantly the acne org regimen. Please don't confuse this with products that make a profit, it's all about how you use whatever you choose

The acne org regimen works wonders. Yes, months after trying these pads I spent some more of my time on google and finally checked out their site. It is more about the regimen itself than the products they sell and they even state that. It's about washing your face, twice a day for roughly 10 seconds (crazy, right?) then waiting 15 min to put on a 2.5 peroxide lotion, then 15 more and putting on a regular moisturizing lotion.

Other tips that helped me... change your pillowcase daily or every other. Use a separate towel for your face and one for your body/hair. Drink enough water. And one you've heard 1000x over, don't touch your face.

These wonder products are scams. A bunch of poor saps are paid hourly to leave reviews for products like these. It's sad because people like us suffered long enough then get screwed over and over and over hoping that something will work. Good luck, people!

column6: Suave Kids 2 In 1 Shampoo and Conditioner, Purely Awesome Mango
column13: Not as overpowering as their watermelon kids shampoo
column14:
I've been using various Suave products for my son's hair since he was a toddler. He's 11 now, but still likes the tear free products, so I thought I'd give this one a shot as he was tired of the "watermelon" smell of the last one he had.

This one works alright, pretty much on par with the others. It really is tear free, didn't bother his eyes when he tested that feature for me (after a hefty bribe of some extra video game time). The smell is pleasant, not really identifiable as any one specific thing, and is less overwhelming than the watermelon smell in the other version we have. It's nice without being rude about it.

Stands on its head just fine, but as with their other bottles I've had, the opening is a bit aggressive. It's too easy for kids to squeeze the dickens out of it and end up with way more product than they'd need in a week. I would've preferred something that had a slower flow.

But it does a good job, lathers well and rinses out about as easy as any. They just need to make the holes smaller.

column6: Mally Beauty Liquid Light Eyeshadow Trio
column13: Bulletproof, smudge-resistant, extremely long-wear eyeshadow that goes on light and fresh
column14:
The name is misleading b/c it doesn't truly capture the technology of this product: Liquid Light is an innovative "transforming" liquid-to-powder that bursts upon application and sets to a long-wear, transfer-resistant, smudge-proof finish.

The secret lies in the individual particles of powder: Each particle contains fresh water that cools and evaporates (so the layer is ultra-thin, barely-there, undetectable feel), leaving behind the pure color. It's refreshing to feel the water droplets break and then transform into the shimmering color that lasts literally till the next day -- it's almost impossible to rub off/smear yet breaks down easily with an oil-based makeup remover/cleanser.

Brown - shimmery neutral brown for all skin tones, similar to an Urban Decay shade, perfect for everyday or smoky eyes
Plum - shimmery pale lavender that works great as a lid wash
Champagne - light golden bone shimmer that works as a highlighter or every day natural shadow

If you demand long-wear and "bulletproof" qualities in your makeup that will last in heat and sweat -- yet feels airy and light, then this is your potion.

column6: Jungleman All-Natural Deodorant, Unscented - 3.0 Ounce Stick
column14: I absolutely love this deodorant.  I've been using it for over four years, maybe five now, heck I was probably one of their first customers.  I wanted a deodorant that was free of aluminum and any other chemical I couldn't pronounce and also worked to control odor.  I looked into making my own deodorant, and would have probably tried that, but then I stumbled across Jungleman and was pleased to see this had the same ingredients as I would have used to make my own except I didn't have to go to the trouble.  I ordered it and found it to be extremely simple and effective for me and the rest is history.  There was a period of time a couple years ago when the product was not available (I think the owners were reevaluating their business or something).  I had used up my last stick and needed to reorder but couldn't find it.  So at that time I tried several other "all natural" deodorants from the health food store or online and I hated them all.  None of them ever came close to the odor control power of Jungleman.  After a couple months of using these terrible deodorants I again decided I was just going to have to try to make my own.  I tried one last search for Jungleman at the time and there it was, back on the market!  I ordered like 5 sticks at once and thanked the owners profusely for bringing it back.  They had changed their formula slightly (I could tell it was more oil and less dry) but it still worked great for me so I continue to be an avid supporter.  I am now ready to reorder once again and am happy to find Jungleman easily available on Amazon and I see they have more varieties available as well.  I hope they have not changed their original formula again as I loved it just the way it was!  If necessary I will post an update when my new stick arrives.  I love that you CAN be all natural and odor free at the same time!

column13: Best wax I've found in 20 years
column14: I was a professional speed waxer in my last career, and I have used all kinds of wax over the years. I usually use a honey type wax, always thinking that the cream style waxes wouldn't grab enough hair to do the job. Boy was I wrong. This product is terrific! I have very fine, blonde body hair, mainly from exclusively waxing and not shaving for the last two decades, so this may not be grabby enough for coarse hair, but it worked great for me. I like that it contains titanium dioxide and moisturizers, as it was really easy to see any left on my skin, and it was essentially painless. I prepped my legs with cornstarch based powder prior to waxing, and used natural muslin strips. I was not left with any sticky residue, clean up was a breeze with plain coconut oil, and I had no redness. This wax is fantastic, and such a great bargain. I also bought sample bags of the different hard waxes for bikini and underarms, and I can't wait to try them too. Thanks for a great product!

column6: Paraffin Wax Works  Treatment, 1 Pair
column14:
This is an excellent portable paraffin wax treatment. I really love how it makes my hands feel really silky and smooth. I can't really do anything when these are on my hands, but they feel nice and I like relaxing with them. Also, the black heart on the outside actually turns red when the wax gets really hot. I used mine in the microwave, and it worked really well.

They have a unique design, which is basically a plastic hand wrapper that has a spongy interior, and the sponge holds all of the paraffin wax so that it delivers it right to your hands. It also stays hot for a pretty long time, which surprised me that all the heat didn't dissipate really quickly.

These are made for average hands, so if your hands are giant, then these might be hard to fit into. But, they should work pretty well for most hands. Also, they're great for the first treatment, but for subsequent treatments, it's really tough to keep the wax in the sleeve while microwaving.

But, overall, they're awesome for disposable paraffin treatments.

Pros:
+Makes your hands feel silky smooth
+The spongy interior absorbs and holds most of the wax
+The heat indicator really works

Cons:
-May not last a full five treatments

*TGN gave me this wax to review*

column13: ... old school style of shaving since I wasn't very pleased with the amount of $ I was spending monthly ...
column14: I decided to return to the old school style of shaving since I wasn't very pleased with the amount of $ I was spending monthly on razors, plus i am military and required to shave EVERY day. The razor was versatile, well crafted of quality steel and a great price. The price for 5 razors at target are $3.50, the blades are well crafted( made in Deutschland of course!) and I couldn't get a better shave. These razors actually shave you- new razor heads currently in the market pull and then cut the hairs on your beard leaving ingrown hairs, cuts and razor burn. I recommend using the weight of the head while shaving for momentum and always rinse it off in warm water and towel dry the razor . I highly recommend this product and its well worth its investment of $30! you wil save at least $200= a years in newer style razor blades that just wear out and cost $17 for 5 blades.

column13: although I love Ancient Minerals Magnesium lotion
column14:
Here's why this 5 star product only got 3 stars from me...

Because the dispenser should have a pump. It's impossible to get product out of this bottle after it's been used for awhile for two reasons. The bottle is too stiff to squeeze. The product is too thick to pour out of the container. I wind up having to bash the bottom of the bottle to get it to flow towards
the opening....or I have to take off the cap and slam the bottle against the side of my (clean) sink so some of the lotion lands in the sink and
then I can use my hand to grab a decent amount of product....so I can apply it to my skin. I find this process of using the product very frustrating

....this to be oxymoron packaging....although I love Ancient Minerals Magnesium lotion....It helps me sleep well and helps with muscular aches and pains...
BUT I cannot give a manufacturer high ratings if I'm frustrated using their product.

column7: This product delivers such a gentle, thorough cleansing, maybe it should be called something other than "soap"! It's called "body soap" but I also used it on my face and loved the result. After cleansing, the skin feels dewy soft and moisturized as well as really clean, almost as if no additional lotion or moisturizer is needed - although I am looking forward to the soon to come Christina Moss body lotion. I really like that the soap isn't fragranced, another reason maybe it should be called something other than "soap" - because almost every soap on the market has added fragrance (even if it's a so-called "natural" fragrance); this soap doesn't, there is absolutely NO added scent! I will be a repeat customer and anticipate sampling additional Christina Moss products.

column6: keratin Treatments
column13: Would I buy and do it again?
column14: Some background: My hair is VERY heat damaged. Due to thyroid ussues, it is also VERY dry, brittle and falling. I have THICK wavy hair yet the strands are not thick. Doing this was a last option before chopping my long hair  (mid back lenght). I'm also challenged in all thing beauty (don't know how to apply makeup,  do my eyebrows or different hairstyles if you get my drift.) I have had 2 professional keratins before and loved the result but don't have that kind of money anymore.  Here is how it went for me: First of all it took me a good 3.5 hours (did I mention I was all-things-beauty challenged?) But I didn't want to rush and loose my money or worse, end up bald. The claryfying shampoo left me looking like a tumbleweed. My hair was so dry after that shampoo it was rough to the touch. I almost shaved my head at the point. I blow dried, detangled and got to it. I did wear gloves but didn't have a "coloring brush thingy". I went to my backdoor porch. I was expecting to suffocate and my eyes to burn. My experience was the it actually smells good (like coconut vanilla yogurt). I had done the back part of my hair with no smell. However, the closer I got to my face was when I felt the fumes people speak of on the reviews but since I was outside at 8 am, it was bearable and it didn't take me long to finish at that point since it was only the sides and top of my hair.  While straightening, the smell got better. There was a lot of smoke coming out of my hair and by now I was doubting if I was doing all of this right and if it was worth it. When I finished my hair felt a bit "waxy" but also soft and was pin straight and shiny. I was beyond happy with the results. I hadnt been that hapoy with my hair in a long time. I'm on day 2. I will update on what happens after I wash.  Would I buy again? Probably. The results are great, my hair is not frizzy or looks dry anymore and it's not even falling off. And I still have a half bottle even with my thick hair!!! I'mexpecting it won't last me the full 4-6 months I get out of the salon version because my hair wasn't as bad as it was at this point. But if I can get at least 2 months out of it,  it's worth the time and "trouble". I did end up with some aching arms and shoulders but if I did this successfully, anyone (and I do mean ANYONE) can do this! Hope this helps someone.

column6: Uriage Bariésun SPF 50+ Fragrance-Free Cream 50ml
column13: A very good broad protection susncreen with no white cast
column14: I am a fan of European sunscreens because of the Tinsorbs and Uvinuls, which we don't have in the US.  The provide very good UVA/UVB protection. This also has antioxidants.  US sunscreens don't have these superior ingredients.  Zinc is also good, but it breaks me out. If you are looking for a  non-mineral suncreen that his highly stable but doesn't have avobenzone, this is a good option.  Avobenzone is a good UVA sunscreen, ,but it must be stabalized and the mineral sunscreens in make up can make it less stable.  This has no avobezone, so I can wear this with a makeup with sunscreen (most have SPF) and not worry.  This is best for those with dry skin.  If you use the full amount it feels like you are putting on a lot of light cream.  I end up looking wet for a bit but then it settles down. It doesn't feel like nothing. It ends up feeling like a light coating of moisturizer, which I like with dry skin. Also lets me know it's still there. I don't want to be greasy though and don't with this. No fragrance or white cast. Gentle and effective.  Might not suit oily types, or people who hate the feeling of anything on their skin or want something mattifying might prefer something else. .  Pretty tenacious too.  I feel protected walking around in summer with this, but I still wear hats and take care.

column6: Turquoise, Antique Bronze, and Silver Womens Prime Knuckle Ring Set (8 Pack)
column14:
I had never heard of knuckle rings before I learned about them through this review opportunity. They are what they say they are...rings that fit on your knuckles! This set that I received came with 4 silver rings and 4 brass rings.

The rings come in different sizes so some/most of them are sure to probably fit on at least some fingers! I was able to fit each of the 8 rings on all of my fingers. Depending on what fingers I used them on, some of them fell off of my fingers because they were too loose, while others stayed securely on my fingers. They will most likely be a conversation starter since I do not think a lot of people know about them, even though they have been popular in the past (back in the Old Renaissance times).

I received this product free in exchange for an honest and unbiased review

column13: The earrings themselves are beautiful, and shiny for the most part aside from ...
column14:
Let me start by just saying that I received a discount to purchase these earrings for a review.

I am completely dissatisfied with the shipping time. Even though thy came from China, they still took longer to arrive than the alloted scheduled time. When I did finally receive them they came in a small unprotected envelope. You would think that coming from so far the seller would at least put them in a small box to keep them from becoming damaged.

The earrings themselves are beautiful, and shiny for the most part aside from the fact that a couple stones were in the package, and not attached to the earrings where they should be.

I still chose to wear them out inspite of the being slightly damaged, and still have received complements for how beautiful they are. They are also very comfortable, I have slept in them, and I don't wake up with pain on the sides of my head.

So overall I'm ok with my order aside from the above stated issues.

column13: The sugilite is a great stone, it help me greatly
column14:
The sugilite is a great stone, it help me greatly. Recently I went overseas and decided to bring it along. I felt energetic and less tired. Even when I am tired, it seem to fade quickly. My negative emotions are greatly reduced when wearing it. I found myself easily brushing aside jealousies, anger or annoyance. Joys and laughter came more easily to me. I like it very very much. Tq for enabling us to meet.

I bought other stone bracelets and some are not very suitable for me. Mind you, it's not the bracelets fault. Some are just not suitable for me. I have weak constituents and body, so some stronger stone, I find them to be to strong and overwhelming for me. For example, I was greatly taken by the healing properties of black tourmaline and decided to buy it. Apparently it was too strong for me, i have great headaches when I put it on.

Bloodstone I bought because it is a March birthstone, apparently it is not suitable for me. For me it seem that intuition seem to be more accurate, which stone felt right then it is the one for me.

That's all I suppose. Forgive the poor English. English is not my mother language or even my second language, I can't truly express what I want to say. Once again thank you for the sugilite bracelet, I like it.

column13: Babeyond Charm Rhinestones Crystal Chain Link Double Ring Is Unique,Sparkles,And Is A Great Gift Idea!
column14:
This Babeyond Charm Rhinestones Crystal Chain Link Double Ring is certainly a beautiful and unique piece. I love that the rings are adjustable so no one should have any problems at all wearing them. The rose design is gorgeous and each rhinestone is placed very beautifully and accurately. Whenever the light touches any of the rhinestones in the right spot it sparkles which definitely makes your hand stand out! I've worn this ring a couple times now since I got it and I haven't had any problems with anything breaking,falling off,or any skin irritations or discoloration. The chain that connects the finger ring and the thumb ring together is a little short for my not so normal sized hand but it's not overly short to where I can't wear it; it just gives a little tug and reminds me that it's still there and to not pull overly hard. You could definitely wear this double ring for any occasion rather formal or casual! This would be a great gift idea unless it's too pretty for you to give away (like I did lol). I would definitely recommend this Babeyond Charm Rhinestones Crystal Chain Link Double Ring!

column6: BriLove Women's Boho Style Multi Strands Shell Simulated Pearl Link Chain Statement Necklace Pink
column13: nice materials and it doesn't tangle
column14:
This is a pretty substantial necklace. It has a lot of weight to it. (It's not *too* heavy, I think, but it is heavy. On the other hand, it doesn't flop around at all!) When they say one of the materials is shell, that is pretty easy to believe. The simulated pearls almost fooled me at first -- they have a slightly irregular shape and I initially thought they were actual (dyed) freshwater pearls. At any rate, I feel like the materials are high quality.

Another thing to note: although this is a multistrand necklace, it didn't tangle up at all during shipping or while I was wearing it. (I was a little worried because of all the knotted threads, but there was no need to be worried.)

The clasp on mine was a little difficult to undo. It's a toggle clasp but it's made of some stone material and it doesn't have a lot of give. However, I was able to get the necklace on and off -- without assistance from someone else.

This is a very summery sort of look. Reminds me of a resort or seaside vacation! I think you'd want a fairly plain or neutral top to wear it with because it does have a lot going on.

Overall, though, I was impressed with the quality of the materials and the lack of tangles.

Product provided by the seller for evaluation purposes.

column6: 925 Sterling Silver Cubic Zirconia Princess Crown CZ Band Ring
column14:
I just received these rings today. I ordered 2 so I could pair them with my engagement ring because, as much as I love my engagement ring, the accompanying bands just don't have any pizzazz. My engagement ring is platinum but, right now, my money is better spent on different things than to replace perfectly good (boring) rings with more expensive rings.
The picture seems to show a more "solid"/thicker ring but these are more dainty and the gems are very tiny but I love the the product more than I loved the picture of the product.
If you like wide bands, I suggest buying 2 and either pairing them up (crown to crown) for a filigree style band. If you like extra wide wedding sets (and can handle slightly sharp tips in between your fingers), place them crown out for a stunning wedding ring set. These are eternity bands so the design goes all the way around the ring. The crown tip you see in the picture is repeated 2 more times for a total of 3 crown tips.
If these are truly sterling silver .925 (I'll let you know in a few days, if they aren't, because I'm severely allergic to base metals.), they are worth more than what I paid for them. Even though the cubic zirconias are so small, the rings are shiny and truly stunning.

The only reason I'm including this next information is because someone else's review said these run small. Typically, I wear a size 9 but I swell so much that I buy everything in 10-11. That way, I never have a problem getting a ring off. I'm not sure how it happened but I ended up ordering 12s. It's not the fault of the seller. I made sure to look and I did, indeed, order 12s. I'm not going to return them though. I may just order another set in a smaller size. I have to say, these do NOT run small. I compared them to several size 11 rings and they're bigger (which they should be since they're 12s). They also fan out, slightly, at the top edges of the crowns so that makes them feel even larger.

column13: Beautiful bracelet - do take care to read the care information on the listing.
column14:
My daughter does a home sales business and lot of people at her last convention had on chunky jewelry. She had mentioned she really wanted to get some chunky jewelry to amp up her look for shows etc. When I saw this bracelet, I immediately thought of her and what she was looking to do with her style. It comes with an adorable bag that has a draw string. It was not in the bag when it arrived the bag was seperate but I really liked that because it is going to allow me to put some of the extra confetti like stuff in the bag with it to give to my daughter as a gift. There are very specific cleaning and care instructions on the listing for this item. I highly recommend you use them if you purchase this bracelet. I did notice that someone had posted previously that they had an issue with the color running. I think that is probably why the instructions are listed. In case you can not find them they are below:
Tips to Maintain your accessories:
1) Avoid direct contact with heat, or expose under the sun.
2) Before showering, take out the accessories and keep it in a safe place.
3) Avoid solvents or chemicals like perfume or soap. Dry it with a clean towel if gets wet.
4) Clean in a secure location, not the rim of a sink where a piece may slip down the drain.
5) Use only a soft brush, never sharp or hard objects, to remove dirt or particles.

Keep in mind items that you may use like perfume etc may have alcohol or other agents in it to 'scent' the perfume and may create issues with any jewelry you put on. I try to make sure my perfume has had time to dry before putting anything on where I have applied it.

Overall the bracelet is gorgeous. It is also very sturdy and I am very happy with my purchase as well as the superfast shipping speed!

I work with her mom, and she was telling me how her daughter loved dolphins. They go to San Diego every year so she can swim with the dolphins. I wanted a design that was simple, but elegant. I loved the chain because I felt it was sturdier than a common silver chain. When the necklace arrived, I was beyond impressed. Simple, stunning, sturdy, lovely.The gift box was nice too. She said "This is jewelry, isn't it?" She loved it!. She even wanted to wear it to school. Small expense for big payoff. Thank you! Would order again in a minute. In fact I may get one for myself.

[[VIDEOID:ae6c3e3c33aeaefaf6ad8b906039dad4]]Sent to me for review, this product comes very well presented in a solid mint green gift box with padding and a mint green drawstring bag. It also has a welcome note inside, which I thought was a nice touch. The product is also surrounded by a plastic packet.

From a quality perspective, it's made of high quality material with the materials in question being mainly brass metal and cubic zirconia. It's definitely lightweight and medium sized. Length = 19.5cm / 7.6\\\, Width = 1.2cm / 0.5\\\\\", Weight = 18g.

The design on this is modern, classic and vintage and there are about 70 clear diamantés in a wave shape, dotted between the waves are the navy, 18 blue stones. I really like the sparkle / bling that this creates. I also like the blue colour and how smooth it feels on the wrist.

I found that this is more ideal to wear in a formal setting for a special event or art gallery opening for example. This goes well with a smart dress or nice blouse with chinos and a skirt of a darker blue colour, black, silver or white."

[[VIDEOID:10dd9f793b3a8e18791c6134095287ab]]Sent to me for review, this product comes very well presented in a solid mint green gift box with padding and a mint green drawstring bag. It also has a welcome note inside, which I thought was a nice touch. The product is also surrounded by a plastic packet.

From a quality perspective it's made of good quality material with the materials in question being rhinestone and alloy. Admittedly, it's a heavy necklace and is large sized. Chain Length = 42cm / 16.53\\\ to 48cm / 18.89\\\\\"), Pendant Size = 19cm / 7.48\\\\\") X 11cm / 4.33\\\\\". Total weight = 135g.

The design is modern, art deco and glamorous and whilst the stones are peacock blue in colour, there are 2 clear stones on top. There are a number of oval stones and these vary in size, cascading down the neckline. This is an extendable necklace which is always a bonus. The clasp on the necklace is a lobsters claw.

I really like the blue colour on this necklace and I also like the number of stones that it has. I personally found that this was suitable to wear in a formal setting such as a special event or going out for an important dinner. This goes well with a low cut top or dress of a black, white or peacock blue colour."

column13: Simple, Pretty, and No Itchy Red Earlobes!
column14: I have had these earrings since November 2013 and I never take them off. They're simple, pretty, and never bother my ears! I started to get itchy ears from 14kt gold so I went on a search for hypoallergenic earrings and was pleasantly surprised that stainless steel is totally inexpensive! Decided to give these a try because they were and still are such a great deal. I use the middle 3 sizes because the smallest is too small and "sink" into the holes while the big ones are a little too big for my liking. Even for 3 pairs, I think this is a great price. Highly recommended earrings if you react to other metals and want simple, cute, and long-lasting posts!

column6: MICHAEL Michael Kors Women's Cindy Satchel, Black, One Size
column14: I ordered this because it was large enough to carry all the things I seem to stuff in a purse, had the simple design I prefer and the handles were round which I find easier to deal with than flat strap handles. The leather doesn't seem or feel like leather, but I love the texture, grey-black (close  up) color and the fact it is probably water resistant.  The zipper is great and is easy to open, as is the inner side zipper pocket.  I would have rated it a 5 star except that the material is not stiff enough to carry items I need without obvious "dents" or almost puckering of the ends of the purse when it is 1/2 or really full.  After it is emptied, however, the original shape reappears.  I really like it, BUT: I was hoping to use this as both an everyday-use purse and a semi-formal occasion purse, but would not re-order because of the structural issue described.  Hopefully M Kors will someday sell a purse with this design and size using either a different material or with some structural feature that prevents the puckering and bulging.

column13: Worst Sandals I've Worn For Hot & Humid Florida Summer!
column14:
Bought a pair of these sandals in Mushroom color in size 9 wide width. Disappointment when I wore these sandals at the pool, at the beach. Living in Central Florida, summer lasts April - Mid - October, it get hot and humid. Its season to spend time at the pool, at the beach. Sandals are must have foot wear. This type, style of Crocs sandals were a disappointment for me. The color was ugly. The sandals are cheaply made of plastic molded one piece thong glued to a white sole that is painful to the soles of my feet. The white peebled raised designs on the sandals soles are little hard plastic "dots," hurt as my feet pressed onto the soles. No massaging action - hurts almost like walking bare footed on tiny real peebles. Bottom soles are hard plastic wedge design with basic plastic formed tread on bottom. These sandals are not slip proof!
Poor design, cheap materials, cheap construction, uncomfortable for average woman's feet, fit isn't consistent with other shoe fit sizes. Materials, construction, fit, won't last a normal summer's wear.
If you want to torture your feet then go ahead and buy a pair of these cheap sandals, also you are wasting your money & closet space.

column6: Xloop Running Cycling Sunglasses with White Malibu Eyewear® Microfiber Pouch
column13: Designed to stay on the face of even the most active person
column14:
The Xloop Running & Cycling Sunglasses are designed to stay on the face of even the most active person. They have a unique design to them that is made to move with you without hindering your activity. The sides of the sunglasses that are normally hugging your face near your temples are out a little further than they would be normally giving you added room and comfort, yet the pivot style arms ensure a snug fit that keeps the glasses securely in place and prevents slipping.
The lens is a dark smoke with a mirrored finish that reflects a bluish purplish tint to it. It is a single lens that wraps around and gives complete coverage and protection from sun and dust during your favorite outdoor sports. The bottom of the lens is contoured with the curves of your cheeks. The nosepiece is made up of two separate rubberized pieces. Overall these glasses are well made and have a stylish look to them. I received this product for free in exchange for my honest, unbiased review.

column6: Hotson Shoe Men's Low Top Black Leather Sneaker Classic Footwear Size 10
column14: These are OK shoes. Nice minimal design. Won't be mistaken for a pair of Common Projects, but neither will the price. The leather is stiff and requires some break-in, but they're wearable. Perhaps the biggest weakness is what's on the inside. The sockliner is made of a flimsy piece of cloth that is in no way bound to the footbed. While in most shoes this is not a problem, this piece represents the only solid platform for the foot. The footbed itself is sort of like a honeycomb of hollow rubber with a supporting 'grid.' After a few days wearing these shoes, the heel started caving in and the sockliner fell apart. I may try a pair of store-bought insoles, but odds are these shoes are heading for the garbage long before I expected they would. Disappointing only begins to describe it. If you're after a pair of decent minimal leather sneakers, do yourself a favor and keep looking. You'll find better construction at your local Payless (at a much lower price). In the $50 price range, just pick up a new pair of Stan Smiths.

column6: Dunham Men's Lawrence Steel Toe Boot
column13: A full year walking in my shoes.
column14: I just hit the one year mark wearing these boots. I am tempted to buy them again but not for the comfort factor. I still think this boot is the best looking steel toe work shoe I have seen and I've looked at a lot of them. Style and weight are the main reasons why I purchased it a year ago. Even though this is a higher topped shoe, it is considerably lighter than a Timberland low-top shoe I had previous to this one (The Titan).  And that is a contributing factor of why I would purchase it again this year. The other reason I am considering it again is durability. The stitching, leather and everything about it on the upper has held up well...really well. I think the sole has a little more wear on the heel than I would expect but it hasn't fallen apart, worn down so much that is smooth/slick, started "flapping" or anything like that. In other words, if the upper would get me a couple years, which I think it would, it is doubtful the sole would.  As far as comfort? These boots are not really comfortable. To be fair, there are very few shoes I find comfortable, so part of that is me and part of it is the shoe. There seemed to be a couple of hot spots in the foot bed. I knew this going in and knew I would need to put an orthotic in the boot—which I did—a $30.00 orthodtic. This made the comfort level tolerable.  Another thing to consider, depending on where you live is: This is a hot boot. I live in SW Florida, so hot boot is not necessarily a good thing. All waterproof work boots may be hot, I don't know. I know I appreciated the warmth of the boot this past winter but haven't been too fond of it this summer. As far as waterPROOF goes, I don't think so. It is very water resistant but not waterproof. I have spilled/poured water a couple of times right on the area where the tongue begins and got a wet-ish foot. I have no complaints with their waterproof claim, however,  when it comes to walking through puddles, wet grass, etc. They perform well there.  I get a boot allowance from work of $100.00 per year (or as needed). If I didn't get that, I doubt very much that I would have bought this boot, considering I have to add the orthodic just to make it comfortable. Again, some of this dissatisfaction is probably me. Will I buy it again? Probably not this year since I since I have a considerable amount of life left in them. I cleaned them up and oiled them yesterday and they still look pretty dang good. I think this year I will go with a Keen brand shoe that I tried and liked. It is a low shoe-type steel toe. I wanted to have a lighter shoe that I can wear the times when I have inside work and have these boots for rougher outside type work. I would say I work 50/50 inside/outside. If the Keens hold up well this year, I will probably buy these Dunhams again next year to try and maintain a couple pairs of shoes to switch off with. If they were more comfortable, lighter, cooler and closer to a hundred bucks, I would buy them right now!

column6: Altra Running Womens Olympus 1.5 Trail Running Shoe
column14: I've been walking somewhere between 5 and 6 miles at a time and so far, my feet are doing well.  I feel like as if I'm walking on on pillows!  Two years ago when I trained for a walking race, I went to the local recommended athletic shoe store, only to be sold the worst shoes imaginable.  I have pes planus (flat feet) as well as stage IV chondromalacia in both knees, so knew I needed the correct shoe/arch support to avoid further problems. But even with my "preventative" approach, within weeks, I developed plantar fasciitis,  The condition is no longer present, but this year, I've gone and done my own research, and I am happy with my choice.  The widened/box toe area gives me enough space to spread/fan out all my toes comfortably!  I tell my patients that shoes on your feet are alot like the tires on your car, so choosing wisely and knowing what is needed can make all the difference in avoiding foot, knee or back pain!  Granted, I wear these shoes for walking, not running. so take that into consideration. If I had one preference, it would be to have a little bit more ankle support.  All I know is, I have no plans to ever need foot or knee surgery!!  I will be looking into the Hoka One One brand next.

column6: ASICS Women's GEL-Kahana 6 Trail Running Shoe
column14:
It's my first time to try ASICS trail running shoes and I feel comfortable with this pair in general. Try it again in rainy weather yesterday, and find it horribly slippery when I stepped on wet rock - I go hiking almost every weekend, and am fine in all weather basically; yet I have never encountered such slip with other shoes before. I won't recommend it to newbies but personally, I will keep trying it to learn to improve my stepping skills :)
Perhaps the shoes have been produced for a few years, so the rubber has already been deteriorating and the toe tip of my right shoe got slightly worn out after wearing it for a whole day in the first time. Provided the relatively cheap price, it is not bad to give it a try - also a good lesson to pick trail running shoes next time.

column6: ASICS Women's GT-1000 3 Running Shoe
column13: Handsome shoe but not a true \wide\""
column14: I'm a size 9 (occasionally a half-size down or up) over-pronator with a wide forefoot and an average heel, so I look for stability, motion control, and arch support in a running shoe in a wide size (D).  I've had good experiences with some men's Asics in a medium width, but I liked the looks of this women's shoe so much that I decided to try it.  I do love the looks, but alas, the D size isn't a true wide, which I can usually wear:  while the size-9 length of these fits me well, both the toe box and midsection are so narrow that the shoe is too snug even with thin socks.  They are extremely breathable because they're mesh, but because of that I'm not sure they'd stretch enough even with a professional stretcher to be wearable with crew socks, and they'd be quite uncomfortable to work out in.  Correction:  I got these in a size 9.5.  So even though I'm normally a size 9, that would be way too tight in this shoe.  Also, perhaps because they're all-mesh, they don't offer as much stability and cushioning as most of the Asics I've had, which is surprising, considering that on another website the manufacturers says they're "Built for mild to moderate overpronator who requires a blend of enhanced cushioning and stability."  I didn't notice either one.  I would have loved to be able to keep these shoes, but I'll have to return them and either go back to wearing men's sneakers or find something in a true wide.  PROS: Beautiful shoe, good price, looks great if you can wear it. CONS:  Not a true wide even if labeled "D"; less cushioning and compensation for pronation than some descriptions indicate.

IMPORTANT INFORMATION: take a pair of your old shoes and on the tongue of most shoes it will say the cm size. For example, my Nikes are size 11 and are 29cm in length. But the Polo shoes I bought are size 10.5 and 29cm in length. So to get the right size find out the cm size of some shoes that fit you comfortably and refer to the size chart to find the right fit for you. column6: New Balance Men's MX857 Cross-Training Shoe
column14:
TERRIBLE QUALITY CONTROL. I've gone through FOUR pairs of shoes in an attempt to get a pair that has the soles of the forefoot and heel on the same plane. I wear orthotics so that my feet strike the ground without twisting. With these shoes the forefoot's sole is not always on the same plane as the heel's. Your heel strikes the ground and then your foot twists (noticeably) to accommodate the forefoot's different sole plane.

On some shoes it was the left foot, on others it was the right foot. New Balance used to be a brand that you could trust to be built properly. I'm sad to say that after 15 plus years as a customer I'm going to have to find another brand to wear.

One last comment. This version of the MX857 is much narrower than my last one, purchased a little over a year ago.

The only bright note has been Amazon's customer service.

column14: The fit and cut are fine - runs true to size (length and width), and they look nice on the feet. But they are soooo hurtful! I first wore these to dinner and to walk around the museum for 2 hours, and my feet hurt but I just thought they needed breaking in. The time after that I wore them to work - I'm not on my feet all day, and I just do moderate walking between desks/cafeteria/bathroom. Ouch! The back of my ankles were bleeding from the shoes rubbing against them the whole day, and I almost died on my walk home by the end of the day. Still not giving up (maybe thinking that after wearing them all day they might have finally been broken in), I wore them and walked to the park (~0.5 mi). They were still uncomfortable and I felt the back of my ankles starting to get raw again... Thank God I brought flip flops to prepare for this scenario. Never again!

My initial reaction was to return these due to the fit but I decided to wear them for a day & see how they felt. After a single day of use, my foot fit much better into the toe area and after two days they fit just like a perfect, normal fit. I think because of the extra "mush", things just take a little time to settle. Allow the mush to form to your feet. Once that happens, these fit like a dream! column6: KEEN Women's Concord Slip On Shoe
column14: The Good:  The Keen Concord Slip-ons were shipped fast!  They are nice looking casual leather street shoes  They are good to wear with jeans or casual work clothing year round.  The footbed fits true to my usual 8.5M shoe size.  There is no way I would increase the size I bought, because then the back of the shoes would slip off my heels while walking.  The Bad:  I understand why some people might not keep these shoes.  They are a bear to get on.  I had to use a long shoe horn and really push my feet into the shoes.  Right out of the box, the leather uppers are extremely tight across my instep and the insoles of the shoes are harder than I expected them to be.  Final Note:  I am keeping these shoes because they so look nice, are made well and  were value priced when I purchased them.  I think they will break in and loosen up to conform to my feet and work out just fine for me.  Eventually, I hope to be able to wear regular socks with them to add extra cushion and warmth in cold weather.

column6: Cole Haan Women's Calixta Ankle Boot
column13: Not a comfort shoe for me
column14:
Love the look of these boots, but for me, they are not nearly as comfortable as everyone else seems to be experiencing. There is supposedly some kind of fancy technology in these boots, but it didn't work for me. By the end of the day, I was taking them off and wearing my slippers around the office just to go get a drink of water. It's not like they're painful or anything - it's just that "I want to walk like a normal person now" feeling you get after wearing shoes that aren't right for your feet for a while.

I put some ball-of-foot cushions in mine so that hopefully these can still be my go-to Fall booties as I was expecting they would be.

The sole is rubber, but a very solid, inflexible kind that probably contributes to the less-than-stellar comfort. Maybe people who wear stilettos all the time are the ones saying these are so comfortable, but I'm all about comfort, so these were an unpleasant surprise on my feet.

column6: Shoes8teen Shoes 18 Womens Canvas Shoes Lace up Sneakers 18 Colors Available
column14:
After reading mixed reviews i'm surprised that I really like these shoes. I am flat-footed & have issues with my feet so i'm kinda picky about shoes. I normally only wear select brands of shoes that I know work for me. I bought a few other cute looking cheap no-brand-name shoes on Amazon & the others all got sent back for one reason or another. I honestly fully expected these shoes to have something wrong with them (look cheap-o, make my feet hurt by pressing on my bunions or rubbing blisters on my heels, have super slick soles or a funky smell, etc.) but i am happy to report that they are totally normal & really cute!

I bought them in Aqua and it is a beautiful color. The materials seem to be good quality, although there are these weird little round "plugs" on the soles (see my pics). Fortunately they do not affect how the shoes feel or cause any problems. The soles are flat, no arch (which i prefer) but there is a bit of cushioning to the insoles (which i also prefer) so they are pretty comfy. If i still worked in retail pulling 8+ hr. shifts on my feet i probably wouldn't wear them, however for normal everyday wear they are great. I can run errands around town or wear them to my current job as a part-time nanny with no problem. :)

As for the fit, the length is ok but they seem a bit wide. I thought about returning them to go down 1/2 a size so they would fit snugger, but my usual size 8 in women's fits me fairly well length-wise and i feared that the 7.5 might not be long enough. So i kept the 8's. If I leave them loosely laced they feel sloppy, but as long as I pull the laces tight enough they are fine. I am actually thinking about getting a few other pairs in other colors.

column13: but it seems like some of the gold print was scratched off on ...
column14: *Update Seller exchanged with me a new pair! The quality is a lot better and the glasses seem more authentic. The RB engraving is now regular. Also I actually just bought another pair at sunglasses hut, and I found that indeed all the cases have this little pocket in between...which I find weird but doesn't actually negatively affect the case's function. It seems like the case color is random as well I received a brown this time when I exchanged it.  ****Next Day Update : 2 stars So actually I looked a bit closer and the RB engraving seems off. The letters aren't etched with equal weight. The center of the B has a white spot thats actually pretty visible and distracting. I also noticed small nicks on the bottom of the frames. I am going to return this pair for an exchange and update my review when I get them ****** Original 3 Stars I ordered the RB2132 New Wayfarer 710/51 52-18 2N from Vision Group, fulfilled by Amazon.  On the RB website these retail for $140.  The box I received was had wrinkles in each corner. For SOME reason they had to put the Amazon bar code ON the RB Serial Information on the box. I had to peel it to make sure that this was the right model. Of course the sticker destroyed most of it, but I could make out a 2N 710/51 and 52 so I guess it's the right one.  The contents of the box include the glasses with 1 sleeve of plastic on 1 temples (not both or together), 1 black case with a gold seal, 1 RB cloth, and 1 RB Manufacturer's note.  The cloth I got seems to be a little bit off, the zig-zag cut pattern is not even on all sides and the redness of the logo seems a dark magenta red vs. the cherry red seen on the box/booklet/website.  The case I got is okay. The gold seal is shiny, but it seems like some of the gold print was scratched off on the inner ring. The WORST part seems to be that the case may be coming apart.  The glasses, however based on my comparison to a few youtube videos seem authentic. All small details are present and they have a good feel.

column6: Rikio Fighter Black Jikatabi (Outdoor Tabi) - Size 28
column13: Great minimalist shoe. Only one problem....
column14: Great minimalist shoe. Only problem is, no half sizes for people with over size 8 feet. I was caught in the middle; 28 was far too small and 29 was too big, floppy and insecure. So, I returned mine... Good to remember that these fit like gloves, so it's important to use their size chart and select a size close to your own foot measurement. Otherwise great shoe, sole is so flexible that if I hold the shoe with the sole parallel to the ground it will droop towards the floor. If you're a minimalist runner/enthusiast you know this is a very good thing. The sole has a very high percentage of rubber and traction is extremely good, no excessive wear but, because of the composition of the sole I avoid too much use on pavement for the pair I kept(29). Putting the shoe on is not complicated or difficult; you start from the bottom and hook the metal tabs(kohaze) to whichever line of string is the most comfortable for you. It's a good idea to flex your foot up while hooking the kohaze as it makes it easier. I recommend getting injinji or tabi socks(non-kohaze) to go with these so you can avoid dirtying the white linen inside. The shoes are not waterproof so keep that in mind, the canvas  upper is tough though. All in all great shoe, if they had half sizes they would be perfect and would get my repeat business. At their best they are nimble, light durable and cool looking minimalist shoes, try them, I recommend it!!

column13: Clear lenses, Great Price, Good Buy
column14: Very clear lenses with sturdy plastic frames. The three colors received were not as pictured in the product item photo though - received solid black, a transparent medium pinkish red and a transparent golden tortoise shell. Don't get me wrong, I like the colors but it would have been helpful to know what they were when ordering. Frames measure 1/4" on side bars, lens frame is 2" wide across and 1" vertical. Comfortable to wear, great price so I can keep pairs wherever needed. Just to be as accurate as possible, the title for this product reads "Classic Reader" but the inside of the side bar of the actual glasses reads "Optx Tradition".  I have previously ordered several packs of 2.0 in Classic Reader and I thought I was ordering the same exact pairs in 2.5 [tough getting old]. However, the Tradition is a little thicker on the side bar at 1/4" while the Classic Reader is 1/8". The frame around the lens is also just a bit thicker on the Tradition. The glasses seem to be a carbon copy of the Classic Reader just overall a tad thicker and therefore sturdier, an improvement.

column14: Read a lot of reviews that mention to go a 1/2 size larger than you normally buy in shoes. I suppose that advice isn't always accurate. Mine were just a tad large. No worries though (I kept the shoe instead of returning for a smaller size). So far the shoe has been great. After wearing them a bit, I figured that if I were to go with the normal size I usually go with, and were to ever wear thick socks with it, it would be too small. This is the reason I haven't bothered returning the product. 2 months later, of non-stop normal wear, and I'm pretty impressed with it. I've taken them on light hikes here and there and the shoes have held up remarkably well. I do want to mention that the traction isn't meant for wet slippery rocks (most hiking shoes/boots aren't anyway), but regardless of that fact, they did a somewhat decent job in that environment.  It does get a 'little' warm, but nothing I couldn't handle, as the breathability of the shoe was good. It wasn't awesome. It wasn't poor. It was just... good. If the breathability was a little better, I would probably give it 5 stars.

column6: NIKE AIR MAX 360 BB LOW (MENS)
column13: Excellent. Comfortable, supportive, and stylish workout shoe!
column14:
(I posted a similar review elsewhere before I found this page--sorry!)

I have owned these for nearly six months, but bought them from a local shop instead of Amazon. Trying on shoes is extremely important to me.

I chose these shoes in size 9 wide. I generally feel I need wides in all styles to accommodate my slightly larger right foot. If it helps the reader to know, I would be fine with medium-width shoes if my feet 'matched'. Also, I have high arches, the 'Egyptian' toe alignment, and a very slight hammertoe on the right foot due to wearing ill-fitting shoes all my life.

I would not say I have 'problem feet', but there are enough problems to make shoe-shopping an annoyance. That is why I am so impressed with these shoes, which were the most comfortable out of at least a dozen athletic styles I tried on, many also Nikes.

I have been deeply satisfied with these shoes for my purpose of fitness training. I am lightfooted and bouncy when I wear them. The mesh panels feel cool when I need them to, but my feet don't get wet if there's rain on my way to or from the gym. I live in a rainy area! (I wouldn't test this in a serious deluge, or in puddles. It IS mesh.)

Also, the grey and green colour scheme is cute. The green is a sweet minty shade (but greener than shown in the photo) which matches a lot of activewear I've found locally. I love the ability to base many attractive outfits on my shoes.

I walk a short distance to the gym and do my daily workout ranging from cardio to weightlifting, and sometimes I shoot hoops or do a similar activity. These shoes have me fully comfortable and supported throughout. It can be a bit dicey when my feet swell from extended activity or hormonal stuff, but only because of the aforementioned larger size of my right foot. This is rarely a problem, though. If I wanted to have perfect comfort 24/7 in any shoes, I would have to get them custom-made. For an off-the-rack product, the Nike Flex Experience Run 3 in size 9 wide has been most excellent. I intend to buy another pair to replace the current shoes when they've worn out, which I do not anticipate happening for a long time. They seem durable and well-constructed.

I do not recommend paying over $65 for these shoes if you can find them near your home. I think I paid $60 for them, and 60-65 is the most common range I see for this style and colour, locally and online. Your experience may vary, of course. Regardless, this is the best athletic shoe I have ever tried!k product, the Nike Flex Experience Run 3 in size 9 wide has been most excellent. I intend to buy another pair to replace the current shoes when they've worn out, which I do not anticipate happening for a long time. They seem durable and well-constructed.
